1
00:02:00,579 --> 00:02:02,998
<i>MAN [OVER PA]:
Ten, nine, eight...</i>

2
00:02:03,165 --> 00:02:05,083
<i>... seven, six...</i>

3
00:02:05,250 --> 00:02:06,585
<i>... five, four...</i>

4
00:02:07,252 --> 00:02:09,213
<i>... three, two...</i>

5
00:02:09,379 --> 00:02:10,589
<i>... one.</i>

6
00:02:22,434 --> 00:02:23,852
[RUMBLING]

7
00:03:07,521 --> 00:03:09,064
[INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER]

8
00:03:22,411 --> 00:03:24,413
[MEN SHOUTING INDISTINCTLY]

9
00:03:54,985 --> 00:03:56,361
MAN:
Dr. Serizawa?

10
00:03:56,987 --> 00:03:59,031
Jerry Boyd. I'm warning you, it's a mess.

11
00:03:59,198 --> 00:04:00,616
It's just a total mess.

12
00:04:00,782 --> 00:04:02,409
Monarch sent me in this morning.

13
00:04:02,576 --> 00:04:04,995
Took a look around,
but I told them we needed you.

14
00:04:07,080 --> 00:04:09,917
JERRY: They picked up a radiation pocket
out here last month.

15
00:04:10,083 --> 00:04:12,669
They got excited, thinking
they had a uranium deposit.

16
00:04:12,836 --> 00:04:15,547
They started stacking up
the heavy machinery and then...

17
00:04:15,714 --> 00:04:17,007
Well, the valley floor...

18
00:04:17,591 --> 00:04:20,344
...collapsed into a cavern below.

19
00:04:20,844 --> 00:04:24,556
Just dropped away. Just gone.

20
00:04:26,600 --> 00:04:30,145
Best guess right now is
about 40 miners went down with it.

21
00:04:37,945 --> 00:04:39,112
This way.

22
00:04:42,407 --> 00:04:46,411
When they first discovered this pocket,
the radiation levels were only half as strong.

23
00:04:47,371 --> 00:04:49,957
It's almost as if contact
with the outside air...

24
00:04:50,123 --> 00:04:53,085
...started catalyzing something.

25
00:05:00,384 --> 00:05:01,969
[CAMERA CLICKS]

26
00:05:02,135 --> 00:05:04,346
Some kind of fossils, right?

27
00:05:05,138 --> 00:05:08,767
I've been digging holes for 30 years,
I've never seen anything like it.

28
00:05:14,273 --> 00:05:17,276
WOMAN:
Oh, my God. Is it possible?

29
00:05:19,111 --> 00:05:20,445
Is it him?

30
00:05:21,071 --> 00:05:22,114
No.

31
00:05:22,281 --> 00:05:24,199
This is much older.

32
00:05:26,368 --> 00:05:29,162
JERRY:
Hey, guys. You gotta see this.

33
00:05:31,123 --> 00:05:33,750
[MAN SHOUTING
IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

34
00:05:41,925 --> 00:05:44,094
[COUNTER CLICKING]

35
00:05:48,599 --> 00:05:50,601
[CLICKING INCREASES]

36
00:05:53,353 --> 00:05:54,563
What is it?

37
00:05:55,689 --> 00:05:57,232
Some kind of egg?

38
00:05:57,983 --> 00:05:59,568
A dormant spore?

39
00:06:03,322 --> 00:06:05,824
The bones are fossilized...

40
00:06:06,783 --> 00:06:09,912
...but this formation seems to be
perfectly preserved.

41
00:06:11,538 --> 00:06:13,373
JERRY:
This one looks broken.

42
00:06:13,540 --> 00:06:14,708
It's like something...

43
00:06:14,875 --> 00:06:16,126
...came out of it.

44
00:06:17,419 --> 00:06:19,296
[HELICOPTER WHIRRING]

45
00:06:22,257 --> 00:06:24,259
[MAN SHOUTING
IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

46
00:06:59,211 --> 00:07:01,213
[MAN SPEAKING IN JAPANESE OVER TV]

47
00:07:03,841 --> 00:07:05,843
[PHONE RINGS]

48
00:07:06,009 --> 00:07:08,053
JOE:
I'll get it. It's probably for me.

49
00:07:11,139 --> 00:07:12,891
[JOE SPEAKS IN JAPANESE]

50
00:07:15,602 --> 00:07:16,937
No, Takashi.

51
00:07:17,104 --> 00:07:20,315
No. Takashi, just listen to me
for a second.

52
00:07:20,482 --> 00:07:23,944
I'm asking for the meeting because
if I have to shut the reactor down...

53
00:07:24,111 --> 00:07:26,655
...you're not gonna want to
read about it in a memo.

54
00:07:27,656 --> 00:07:31,118
I've been following these tremors
since they started in the Philippines...

55
00:07:31,285 --> 00:07:33,412
...and now they're in our own backyard.

56
00:07:33,787 --> 00:07:35,289
No, no, no. Hayato says...

57
00:07:35,455 --> 00:07:38,417
...I need to go through you about this.

58
00:07:38,584 --> 00:07:39,710
Look, I'm just...

59
00:07:39,877 --> 00:07:43,881
...trying to follow the protocols set forth
by the company. That's all. It's my job.

60
00:07:44,548 --> 00:07:45,757
[SOFTLY]
He's awake.

61
00:07:46,383 --> 00:07:48,802
Oh, I know. He got up early.

62
00:07:48,969 --> 00:07:50,012
What are we gonna do?

63
00:07:50,179 --> 00:07:51,221
[SIGHS]

64
00:07:51,388 --> 00:07:52,931
Get dressed. I'll figure it out.

65
00:07:53,348 --> 00:07:55,684
- Okay?
- Okay.

66
00:07:56,310 --> 00:07:58,145
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

67
00:07:58,312 --> 00:07:59,354
Later, Dad.

68
00:07:59,521 --> 00:08:01,648
With all due respect, Takashi, and honor...

69
00:08:01,815 --> 00:08:04,276
...respect and honor, with all of that...

70
00:08:04,443 --> 00:08:07,654
...I'm an engineer. I don't like
unexplained frequency patterning...

71
00:08:07,821 --> 00:08:11,867
...near a plant where I'm responsible.
I need a meeting. Make it happen.

72
00:08:13,327 --> 00:08:14,995
[JOE SPEAKING IN JAPANESE]

73
00:08:17,080 --> 00:08:18,332
Bye, Mom!

74
00:08:18,499 --> 00:08:19,666
[ENGINE STARTS]

75
00:08:21,210 --> 00:08:22,836
He made you a sign.

76
00:08:23,003 --> 00:08:25,464
JOE: What?
- Your birthday sign.

77
00:08:26,590 --> 00:08:28,509
- He worked so hard.
- Oh, God.

78
00:08:30,385 --> 00:08:31,762
SANDRA:
I'm gonna come home early.

79
00:08:31,929 --> 00:08:33,680
I'll take the car and pick him up...

80
00:08:33,847 --> 00:08:35,849
...and we can get a proper cake. Okay?

81
00:08:36,934 --> 00:08:39,186
Listen, I need to know...

82
00:08:39,353 --> 00:08:41,772
...that it's not the sensors. Okay?

83
00:08:41,939 --> 00:08:45,234
I can't be calling this meeting
and look like the American maniac.

84
00:08:45,400 --> 00:08:46,610
So when we get there...

85
00:08:46,777 --> 00:08:50,531
...don't even bother coming up.
Just grab a team and go down to Level 5.

86
00:08:50,697 --> 00:08:51,865
You're not a maniac.

87
00:08:52,032 --> 00:08:54,284
I mean, you are, just not about this.

88
00:08:54,451 --> 00:08:55,827
[JOE GROANS]

89
00:08:56,453 --> 00:08:58,539
Must be something we're not thinking of.

90
00:08:58,997 --> 00:09:00,624
Happy birthday.

91
00:09:02,417 --> 00:09:03,627
What? Is it...?

92
00:09:03,794 --> 00:09:06,213
- Yes, it is. Ha, ha.
- Oh, I forgot all about it.

93
00:09:06,380 --> 00:09:07,798
- Happy birthday.
- Thank you.

94
00:09:08,841 --> 00:09:11,885
I should have a birthday more often. Ha, ha.

95
00:09:12,052 --> 00:09:13,387
[SANDRA LAUGHS]

96
00:09:24,815 --> 00:09:27,234
<i>JOE: What is this?
MAN: Seismic anomaly.</i>

97
00:09:27,401 --> 00:09:29,444
This graph is minutes.

98
00:09:29,945 --> 00:09:32,406
X is minutes, not days. This is now.

99
00:09:32,573 --> 00:09:34,992
Wait, hold on. Seismic activity?

100
00:09:35,158 --> 00:09:37,369
Seismic?
You're talking about earthquakes?

101
00:09:37,536 --> 00:09:39,997
No, earthquakes are random, jagged.

102
00:09:40,164 --> 00:09:42,958
This is consistent, increasing.

103
00:09:44,001 --> 00:09:45,252
This is a pattern.

104
00:09:45,419 --> 00:09:48,463
[WOMAN SPEAKING IN JAPANESE
OVER PA]

105
00:09:50,799 --> 00:09:53,594
All right. Let's make this quick.

106
00:09:54,136 --> 00:09:55,596
[DOOR BUZZES]

107
00:10:02,311 --> 00:10:05,606
Takashi. What the hell is going on?
Have you seen this?

108
00:10:05,772 --> 00:10:07,149
Yeah. Maybe not such...

109
00:10:07,316 --> 00:10:08,901
...good time for a meeting.

110
00:10:11,028 --> 00:10:12,654
JOE:
What's the source?

111
00:10:13,488 --> 00:10:14,948
Where's the epicenter?

112
00:10:15,115 --> 00:10:18,493
TAKASHI: We don't know.
But it keeps getting stronger.

113
00:10:18,660 --> 00:10:20,704
It's gotta be centered somewhere.

114
00:10:21,038 --> 00:10:22,247
Hayato.

115
00:10:22,581 --> 00:10:24,082
No one else is reporting it.

116
00:10:24,791 --> 00:10:27,669
We are contacting every other plant
in the Kantö region.

117
00:10:27,836 --> 00:10:29,421
Tökai, Fujiyama.

118
00:10:29,588 --> 00:10:30,797
They're unaffected.

119
00:10:30,964 --> 00:10:34,885
But my guess is these readings are just
aftershocks from the Philippine earthquake.

120
00:10:35,719 --> 00:10:37,095
Are we at full function?

121
00:10:37,262 --> 00:10:38,305
Yes, we are.

122
00:10:38,680 --> 00:10:42,100
But perhaps we should be
drawing down, to be safe.

123
00:10:42,809 --> 00:10:43,852
[RUMBLING]

124
00:10:46,855 --> 00:10:48,065
Take us offline.

125
00:10:48,232 --> 00:10:49,483
- Now, Joe...
JOE: Do it!

126
00:10:49,650 --> 00:10:51,068
Now. Wind it down.

127
00:10:51,235 --> 00:10:53,487
[SPEAKING IN JAPANESE]

128
00:10:55,113 --> 00:10:56,323
Sandra.

129
00:10:56,490 --> 00:10:57,741
Sandra, are you there?

130
00:10:59,326 --> 00:11:00,953
[WALLS SHUDDERING]

131
00:11:02,913 --> 00:11:04,456
We're turning back.

132
00:11:04,623 --> 00:11:05,666
Let's go.

133
00:11:08,252 --> 00:11:09,837
Oh, my God.

134
00:11:11,630 --> 00:11:12,840
Joe, are you there?

135
00:11:13,006 --> 00:11:16,677
<i>Joe, there's been a breach.
We're heading back to the containment seal.</i>

136
00:11:16,844 --> 00:11:18,846
Listen. You need to get out of there.

137
00:11:19,012 --> 00:11:21,139
<i>If there's been a reactor breach,
you won't last five minutes...</i>

138
00:11:21,306 --> 00:11:23,600
<i>... with or without the suits. Do you hear me?</i>

139
00:11:23,767 --> 00:11:25,269
I hear you. We're coming!

140
00:11:30,691 --> 00:11:31,733
[SHOUTING IN JAPANESE]

141
00:11:32,693 --> 00:11:34,069
JOE:
I'll meet them there myself.

142
00:11:35,112 --> 00:11:36,530
Put the safety doors on manual override.

143
00:11:36,697 --> 00:11:37,781
TAKASHI:
I cannot do that!

144
00:11:37,948 --> 00:11:40,117
JOE: Keep the doors open.
My wife is still in there!

145
00:11:43,412 --> 00:11:44,872
[PANTING]

146
00:11:46,206 --> 00:11:47,833
SANDRA:
Come on, let's go!

147
00:11:57,634 --> 00:11:58,760
[PANTING]

148
00:11:59,219 --> 00:12:00,387
Tell me this door's...

149
00:12:00,554 --> 00:12:01,597
...on manual.

150
00:12:01,763 --> 00:12:03,390
<i>TAKASHl:
Yeah. But we are starting to breach!</i>

151
00:12:03,557 --> 00:12:05,726
I'm here.
Soon as they're through, I'll seal it.

152
00:12:05,893 --> 00:12:07,019
Sandra, can you...

153
00:12:07,186 --> 00:12:08,979
...hear me? I'm at the door.

154
00:12:09,146 --> 00:12:10,189
Sandra?

155
00:12:11,565 --> 00:12:13,108
Sandra, I'm waiting for you.

156
00:12:13,275 --> 00:12:14,818
<i>I'm at the checkpoint.</i>

157
00:12:14,985 --> 00:12:17,696
<i>- But you have to run as fast as you can.
- I am!</i>

158
00:12:18,989 --> 00:12:20,199
[GRUNTING]

159
00:12:23,202 --> 00:12:24,411
SANDRA:
Kenji. Kenji...

160
00:12:24,578 --> 00:12:25,787
...we need to go!

161
00:12:27,498 --> 00:12:28,540
<i>TAKASHl:
Joe!</i>

162
00:12:28,707 --> 00:12:31,126
[SPEAKING IN JAPANESE]

163
00:12:31,293 --> 00:12:32,336
<i>TAKASHl:
Close the door!</i>

164
00:12:32,503 --> 00:12:34,755
<i>Seal the corridor
or the whole city will be exposed.</i>

165
00:12:39,593 --> 00:12:40,802
Sandra?

166
00:12:43,096 --> 00:12:45,432
<i>SANDRA: Joe? Joe, can you hear me?
- Yes.</i>

167
00:12:45,974 --> 00:12:49,186
<i>- Are you there?
- Sandra, I'm here. Can you hear me?</i>

168
00:12:49,811 --> 00:12:51,396
<i>Yeah.</i>

169
00:12:51,563 --> 00:12:54,316
<i>Joe, it's too late. We're not coming.</i>

170
00:12:54,483 --> 00:12:56,443
No, don't say that! Don't you say that!

171
00:12:56,610 --> 00:12:58,403
Run as hard as you can, honey.

172
00:12:59,988 --> 00:13:01,949
<i>Joe, you have to close the door.</i>

173
00:13:02,115 --> 00:13:04,493
<i>You have to live for our son.</i>

174
00:13:06,370 --> 00:13:07,746
[RUMBLING]

175
00:13:08,205 --> 00:13:11,542
<i>TAKASHl: Joe, seal the door! Now!
- Oh, my God.</i>

176
00:13:11,708 --> 00:13:13,252
<i>Five seconds! Four seconds!</i>

177
00:13:13,418 --> 00:13:14,920
[SCREAMING]

178
00:13:20,050 --> 00:13:22,052
[ALARMS BLARING]

179
00:13:25,055 --> 00:13:26,849
[SOBBING]

180
00:13:27,975 --> 00:13:29,017
[BANGING]

181
00:13:30,185 --> 00:13:32,521
[BANGING CONTINUES]

182
00:13:40,988 --> 00:13:42,489
I'm sorry.

183
00:13:45,534 --> 00:13:46,910
[GASPS]

184
00:13:49,580 --> 00:13:51,039
[PANTING]

185
00:14:01,800 --> 00:14:03,010
Take care of Ford.

186
00:14:05,345 --> 00:14:07,431
[SOBBING]
Be a good father.

187
00:14:07,598 --> 00:14:10,350
- I will.
- We didn't make it.

188
00:14:14,021 --> 00:14:16,023
[SOBBING]

189
00:14:20,402 --> 00:14:22,237
[STRUCTURE GROANING]

190
00:14:22,404 --> 00:14:24,281
[ALL SHOUTING]

191
00:14:29,995 --> 00:14:31,580
[ALARM RINGING]

192
00:14:31,747 --> 00:14:33,165
[SPEAKS IN JAPANESE]

193
00:14:33,332 --> 00:14:34,416
Let's go out!

194
00:14:37,252 --> 00:14:41,131
TEACHER:
Hurry! Come on! Ford!

195
00:14:51,141 --> 00:14:53,143
[ALL SCREAMING]

196
00:15:13,372 --> 00:15:14,748
MAN:
On your feet!

197
00:15:18,293 --> 00:15:20,295
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

198
00:15:21,713 --> 00:15:23,465
You got family waiting for you?

199
00:15:23,632 --> 00:15:24,883
I hope so.

200
00:15:25,050 --> 00:15:26,343
How long you been away?

201
00:15:26,510 --> 00:15:27,928
Fourteen months.

202
00:15:28,095 --> 00:15:29,137
Take it slow.

203
00:15:29,304 --> 00:15:31,515
It's the one thing they don't train you for.

204
00:15:32,266 --> 00:15:34,226
MAN:
All right! Let's go!

205
00:15:35,978 --> 00:15:37,855
SAM: I can't tell you.
FORD: Can I see it?

206
00:15:38,021 --> 00:15:39,231
ELLE:
Don't let him see.

207
00:15:39,815 --> 00:15:42,109
FORD:
Whoa. Oh, my God.

208
00:15:42,276 --> 00:15:44,695
ELLE: It's a welcome home cake.
- Look at that.

209
00:15:44,862 --> 00:15:45,904
That's you.

210
00:15:46,071 --> 00:15:48,740
- And that's me.
FORD: What's it say?

211
00:15:49,199 --> 00:15:50,409
"Welcome home, Daddy."

212
00:15:50,576 --> 00:15:51,618
FORD:
Daddy's home.

213
00:15:51,785 --> 00:15:53,745
ELLE: Daddy's home.
- Cake every night.

214
00:15:53,912 --> 00:15:56,707
- Yeah, that's not happening.
FORD: Daddy's home equals...

215
00:15:56,874 --> 00:15:57,916
...cake every night.

216
00:15:58,083 --> 00:16:01,044
How did you manage to get chocolate
on your eyeball?

217
00:16:01,211 --> 00:16:02,254
- Daddy did it.
- Heh.

218
00:16:02,713 --> 00:16:03,922
<i>FORD:
I can't sleep with you...</i>

219
00:16:04,089 --> 00:16:05,674
...making all this noise.
- Hee-hee-hee.

220
00:16:07,301 --> 00:16:09,428
Come on, let's get you into bed.

221
00:16:10,637 --> 00:16:11,680
Okay, big man.

222
00:16:12,931 --> 00:16:14,141
Time to hit the rack.

223
00:16:17,436 --> 00:16:18,645
SAM:
Dad?

224
00:16:19,313 --> 00:16:20,355
Yeah?

225
00:16:21,148 --> 00:16:23,400
Are you still gonna be here tomorrow?

226
00:16:24,776 --> 00:16:25,819
Yeah.

227
00:16:26,778 --> 00:16:28,530
Come on, let's get some sleep.

228
00:16:31,950 --> 00:16:34,661
FORD: Turns around, nose-to-nose,
he says, "At ease, lieutenant."

229
00:16:34,828 --> 00:16:36,538
[ELLE LAUGHING]

230
00:16:39,458 --> 00:16:41,251
[FORD LAUGHS]

231
00:16:46,256 --> 00:16:48,258
God, I missed your laugh.

232
00:16:50,093 --> 00:16:51,553
I missed you.

233
00:16:58,310 --> 00:16:59,561
FORD:
Mmm.

234
00:17:07,444 --> 00:17:08,487
[PHONE RINGING]

235
00:17:08,654 --> 00:17:09,947
FORD:
Mm-mm.

236
00:17:10,113 --> 00:17:12,616
- I should get that. No, it could be work.
- Mm-mm.

237
00:17:12,783 --> 00:17:15,244
ELLE: I need to get that.
- You don't need to. Come on.

238
00:17:17,788 --> 00:17:18,997
Hello?

239
00:17:20,541 --> 00:17:22,417
Yeah, this is Mrs. Brody.

240
00:17:22,584 --> 00:17:24,711
Tell him you're busy tending to
your husband's needs.

241
00:17:24,878 --> 00:17:26,463
Shh.

242
00:17:27,381 --> 00:17:29,299
Yeah, he's my husband.

243
00:17:29,883 --> 00:17:31,844
FORD:
Tell them we're not gonna buy it.

244
00:17:32,928 --> 00:17:35,472
ELLE: Yes, sir.
Could you just hold on one moment?

245
00:17:35,973 --> 00:17:37,182
It's the consulate.

246
00:17:38,600 --> 00:17:40,686
Joe's been arrested in Japan.

247
00:17:43,814 --> 00:17:45,607
Elle, I can't find my pants.

248
00:17:46,400 --> 00:17:47,860
They're in the other drawer.

249
00:17:49,361 --> 00:17:52,531
So why was he trespassing
in the quarantine zone?

250
00:17:52,698 --> 00:17:54,032
Ugh. Why do you think?

251
00:17:54,199 --> 00:17:56,410
The Ione crusader for the truth.

252
00:17:58,203 --> 00:18:02,124
All his crackpot cuckoo theories.

253
00:18:02,291 --> 00:18:05,586
Your father is a good man.
He just needs your help right now.

254
00:18:05,752 --> 00:18:08,088
Ford, he's lost everything.

255
00:18:08,255 --> 00:18:11,091
Yeah, so did I. But you know what?
I got over it.

256
00:18:11,258 --> 00:18:13,010
Right. I can see that.

257
00:18:13,635 --> 00:18:15,095
[FORD SIGHS]

258
00:18:17,931 --> 00:18:19,766
I'm sorry. It's just...

259
00:18:20,517 --> 00:18:23,437
Every time I let him in close,
he always tries to drag me back.

260
00:18:23,604 --> 00:18:27,316
And I can't. I can't put our family
through that.

261
00:18:29,651 --> 00:18:31,778
Well, he is your family.

262
00:18:33,614 --> 00:18:35,240
Hey. Come here.

263
00:18:40,078 --> 00:18:43,957
You know you're only gonna be gone
for a few days, right?

264
00:18:44,666 --> 00:18:48,003
And then you are gonna
come back to me.

265
00:18:48,754 --> 00:18:50,506
Yeah. Yeah.

266
00:18:51,131 --> 00:18:52,508
[ELLE MOANS]

267
00:18:54,801 --> 00:18:56,553
It's not the end of the world.

268
00:18:56,720 --> 00:18:58,388
[FORD SIGHS]

269
00:19:08,148 --> 00:19:10,692
[CHATTERING IN JAPANESE]

270
00:19:10,859 --> 00:19:12,402
[DOOR BUZZES]

271
00:19:13,737 --> 00:19:15,739
[MAN SPEAKING IN JAPANESE]

272
00:19:18,075 --> 00:19:19,451
Papa.

273
00:19:20,661 --> 00:19:23,288
[MAN SPEAKING ANGRILY
IN JAPANESE]

274
00:19:43,100 --> 00:19:44,142
[EXHALES]

275
00:19:59,825 --> 00:20:01,285
[JOE GROANS]

276
00:20:05,873 --> 00:20:07,291
I don't get many visitors.

277
00:20:08,709 --> 00:20:10,002
Clearly.

278
00:20:10,919 --> 00:20:11,962
This is you here.

279
00:20:14,339 --> 00:20:16,717
Even, uh, Ph.D.'s...

280
00:20:16,884 --> 00:20:19,845
...don't get much teaching English
as a second language.

281
00:20:20,804 --> 00:20:21,930
Here we go.

282
00:20:22,097 --> 00:20:23,223
And a towel.

283
00:20:24,725 --> 00:20:26,393
All right.

284
00:20:26,560 --> 00:20:27,769
So...

285
00:20:28,395 --> 00:20:30,105
...how's the bomb business?

286
00:20:30,272 --> 00:20:32,524
It must be a growth area these days.

287
00:20:32,900 --> 00:20:35,527
It's called "explosive ordnance disposal."

288
00:20:36,653 --> 00:20:38,822
My job isn't dropping bombs.

289
00:20:38,989 --> 00:20:40,657
It's stopping them.

290
00:20:42,576 --> 00:20:43,619
- Dad.
- Hey...

291
00:20:44,620 --> 00:20:46,163
...how's Elle doing?

292
00:20:46,330 --> 00:20:48,415
And Sam. Oh, my God. He must be...

293
00:20:48,582 --> 00:20:50,292
...what? Three? Three and a half?

294
00:20:50,459 --> 00:20:51,960
He's almost 5.

295
00:20:52,753 --> 00:20:55,380
I thought you were over this.
"Echolocation"?

296
00:20:56,298 --> 00:20:58,258
- Oh, hey.
- "Parasitic communication..."

297
00:20:58,425 --> 00:21:01,803
Please don't, if you don't mind.
I have everything the way I like it.

298
00:21:01,970 --> 00:21:04,932
I'm just...
I'm studying bioacoustics.

299
00:21:05,098 --> 00:21:06,934
What were you doing, going back there?

300
00:21:07,100 --> 00:21:10,020
- This trespassing stuff, that was bull.
- You broke the law.

301
00:21:10,187 --> 00:21:11,939
I was trying to get back to our old house.

302
00:21:12,105 --> 00:21:13,649
- In a quarantine zone.
- Precisely.

303
00:21:14,149 --> 00:21:16,985
The new readings are exactly
like they were on that day...

304
00:21:17,152 --> 00:21:18,612
...and I can prove it to you.

305
00:21:18,779 --> 00:21:20,781
With a little luck, if I can get back...

306
00:21:20,948 --> 00:21:22,241
...to the house...

307
00:21:22,407 --> 00:21:26,203
...I can show you and the world this was
not from a natural disaster. This was...

308
00:21:26,370 --> 00:21:27,412
Dad!

309
00:21:30,958 --> 00:21:32,543
[KETTLE WHISTLING]

310
00:21:43,971 --> 00:21:45,013
[WHISTLING STOPS]

311
00:21:50,978 --> 00:21:52,938
Your mom's out there, Ford.

312
00:21:55,691 --> 00:21:56,733
To me...

313
00:21:57,150 --> 00:21:58,902
...she'll always be there.

314
00:22:03,991 --> 00:22:06,493
They evacuated us so quickly.

315
00:22:08,328 --> 00:22:11,331
I don't even have a picture of her.

316
00:22:12,833 --> 00:22:14,543
This has to stop.

317
00:22:17,671 --> 00:22:20,090
You know I did everything I could.

318
00:22:20,257 --> 00:22:21,383
You know that, right?

319
00:22:26,430 --> 00:22:27,890
Let me take you home.

320
00:22:29,474 --> 00:22:31,268
Come home with me.

321
00:22:32,019 --> 00:22:35,189
I got a little boy who's desperate
to see his grandpa.

322
00:22:37,149 --> 00:22:38,942
We can leave tomorrow.

323
00:22:46,658 --> 00:22:48,869
[MAN SPEAKING IN JAPANESE
OVER RADIO]

324
00:22:49,036 --> 00:22:51,079
[JOE CONVERSING IN JAPANESE]

325
00:23:14,811 --> 00:23:15,854
What are you doing?

326
00:23:20,359 --> 00:23:21,902
I'm heading back out there, Ford.

327
00:23:22,236 --> 00:23:24,321
- No. I don't think so.
- One hour, in and out.

328
00:23:24,488 --> 00:23:25,739
I have to go!

329
00:23:26,490 --> 00:23:28,408
I came back here and wasted six years...

330
00:23:28,575 --> 00:23:31,161
...staring through that barbed wire,
thinking it was...

331
00:23:31,328 --> 00:23:34,873
...a military mistake or some horrible
design flaw they were covering up.

332
00:23:35,582 --> 00:23:36,959
[SIGHS]

333
00:23:38,168 --> 00:23:39,211
One day...

334
00:23:39,378 --> 00:23:42,422
...I met a guy who runs
a cargo boat offshore.

335
00:23:43,257 --> 00:23:46,802
Every day he goes right past
the reactor site.

336
00:23:46,969 --> 00:23:49,972
So he places a couple frequency monitors
on buoys for me.

337
00:23:51,098 --> 00:23:52,140
Two weeks ago...

338
00:23:52,307 --> 00:23:55,185
I check this thing like every other day
just for the kick.

339
00:23:55,352 --> 00:23:58,397
Two weeks ago, I'm tuning in...

340
00:23:59,690 --> 00:24:01,441
...and, oh, my God...

341
00:24:02,067 --> 00:24:03,569
...there it is.

342
00:24:04,820 --> 00:24:08,031
Whatever "it" is that's in there.

343
00:24:08,198 --> 00:24:10,951
Whatever it is they're guarding
so carefully...

344
00:24:12,369 --> 00:24:14,329
...started talking again.

345
00:24:15,372 --> 00:24:18,041
And I mean talking.

346
00:24:18,584 --> 00:24:19,626
Ha, ha.

347
00:24:20,544 --> 00:24:21,587
I have to go back...

348
00:24:21,753 --> 00:24:22,796
...to our house.

349
00:24:22,963 --> 00:24:25,674
I need my old disks, if they're still there.

350
00:24:26,884 --> 00:24:30,637
I need the data to be able to prove
a baseline here...

351
00:24:30,804 --> 00:24:34,349
...that this isn't a fantasy,
that I'm not what you think I am.

352
00:24:35,642 --> 00:24:37,019
I'm gonna find the truth...

353
00:24:37,519 --> 00:24:38,645
...and end this.

354
00:24:38,812 --> 00:24:40,355
Whatever it takes.

355
00:24:41,565 --> 00:24:43,775
Why can't you just let it rest?

356
00:24:44,109 --> 00:24:45,152
[EXHALES]

357
00:24:46,320 --> 00:24:48,447
Because I sent her down there, son.

358
00:24:50,699 --> 00:24:52,409
This wasn't just a reactor meltdown.

359
00:24:52,576 --> 00:24:53,869
I don't wanna hear this.

360
00:24:54,036 --> 00:24:56,121
I know. I know you don't.

361
00:24:57,748 --> 00:24:59,583
But you can't keep running away.

362
00:25:00,083 --> 00:25:03,212
And, son, you can't bury this in the past.

363
00:25:48,632 --> 00:25:50,634
[DOGS BARKING]

364
00:25:56,139 --> 00:25:57,724
[DOG YELPS]

365
00:25:57,891 --> 00:25:59,518
FORD:
What spooked them?

366
00:25:59,893 --> 00:26:02,729
Dad, come on. Let's go.
It's only another two blocks.

367
00:26:08,318 --> 00:26:09,361
Dad!

368
00:26:10,571 --> 00:26:11,822
Are we going home, or what?

369
00:26:14,366 --> 00:26:16,243
Whoa! Hey, what are you doing?

370
00:26:16,410 --> 00:26:17,578
Dad?

371
00:26:18,954 --> 00:26:20,247
It's clean.

372
00:26:21,832 --> 00:26:23,083
I knew it.

373
00:26:24,376 --> 00:26:27,504
The radiation in this place should be lethal,
but there's nothing.

374
00:27:09,546 --> 00:27:10,797
Thank God.

375
00:27:56,593 --> 00:27:58,512
[HELICOPTER WHIRRING]

376
00:28:22,161 --> 00:28:24,163
FORD:
Are they rebuilding the plant?

377
00:28:25,205 --> 00:28:28,250
JOE:
I don't know. I haven't seen...

378
00:28:28,417 --> 00:28:30,377
[VEHICLE APPROACHES]

379
00:28:31,170 --> 00:28:33,547
[CHATTERING IN JAPANESE
OVER RADIO]

380
00:28:34,423 --> 00:28:36,842
[MEN SPEAKING IN JAPANESE]

381
00:29:09,500 --> 00:29:11,919
[MEN SPEAKING IN JAPANESE]

382
00:29:33,106 --> 00:29:35,651
<i>MAN [OVER PA]:
Ten seconds. Ten seconds.</i>

383
00:29:36,151 --> 00:29:38,153
[MEN SHOUTING IN JAPANESE]

384
00:29:47,246 --> 00:29:49,248
[ENERG Y PULSATING]

385
00:30:01,635 --> 00:30:03,971
Seven-point-two seconds
and getting stronger.

386
00:30:04,137 --> 00:30:05,639
We're trending exponentially.

387
00:30:06,098 --> 00:30:07,516
That's our new curve.

388
00:30:08,058 --> 00:30:10,310
WHELAN:
Jesus, it's worse than we thought.

389
00:30:11,311 --> 00:30:12,729
MAN:
Excuse me, Dr. Serizawa?

390
00:30:14,857 --> 00:30:16,733
Two men were just arrested
in the Q-zone.

391
00:30:16,900 --> 00:30:19,736
WHELAN: We've got bigger problems here.
Have Dr. Graham take a look.

392
00:30:19,903 --> 00:30:21,780
She did, sir. She sent me.

393
00:30:22,990 --> 00:30:25,367
One of them says
he used to work here, doctor.

394
00:30:26,577 --> 00:30:28,328
JOE:
You are not fooling anybody...

395
00:30:28,495 --> 00:30:31,165
...when you say that
what happened 15 years ago...

396
00:30:31,331 --> 00:30:32,583
GRAHAM:
Found these disks in his bag.

397
00:30:32,749 --> 00:30:34,501
JOE:
...was a natural disaster.

398
00:30:34,668 --> 00:30:36,170
GRAHAM:
Not sure what to make of them.

399
00:30:36,336 --> 00:30:39,882
Not an earthquake, it wasn't a typhoon.
Okay? So stop...

400
00:30:40,048 --> 00:30:42,217
Look, I'm tired of talking to you
about this.

401
00:30:42,384 --> 00:30:43,510
I want my son.

402
00:30:43,677 --> 00:30:46,889
I wanna see my son.
I wanna know that he's all right.

403
00:30:47,806 --> 00:30:49,892
This guy, this guy knows.

404
00:30:50,350 --> 00:30:51,643
He knows where he is.

405
00:30:51,810 --> 00:30:53,353
[SPEAKS IN JAPANESE]

406
00:30:53,896 --> 00:30:55,606
I want my son.

407
00:30:56,106 --> 00:30:58,567
And I want my bag and disks.

408
00:30:58,734 --> 00:31:01,653
And I wanna talk to somebody
in charge, not you. No, not you.

409
00:31:01,820 --> 00:31:03,614
I'm done talking to you.

410
00:31:04,990 --> 00:31:08,452
All right? You're looking at me right now,
like I'm in a fish tank, right?

411
00:31:08,619 --> 00:31:10,496
Fine. Because I know
what happened here.

412
00:31:10,871 --> 00:31:13,582
And you keep telling everybody
that this place...

413
00:31:13,749 --> 00:31:15,834
...is a death zone, but it's not.

414
00:31:16,001 --> 00:31:17,294
You're lying.

415
00:31:17,461 --> 00:31:19,296
Because what's really happening...

416
00:31:19,463 --> 00:31:22,132
...is that you're hiding something
out there.

417
00:31:23,050 --> 00:31:24,801
I'm right, aren't I?

418
00:31:26,345 --> 00:31:29,389
My wife died here!

419
00:31:31,391 --> 00:31:34,561
Something killed my wife.

420
00:31:35,729 --> 00:31:36,772
And I have...

421
00:31:36,939 --> 00:31:38,398
...a right to know!

422
00:31:39,733 --> 00:31:41,693
I deserve answers!

423
00:31:45,489 --> 00:31:46,990
[SERIZAWA SIGHS]

424
00:31:48,784 --> 00:31:49,910
GRAHAM:
All these items...

425
00:31:50,077 --> 00:31:51,119
...they were found on him.

426
00:31:51,286 --> 00:31:54,581
- And the date. Look, 15 years ago.
SERIZAWA: I thought all of the data...

427
00:31:54,748 --> 00:31:56,750
...from that day was lost.

428
00:31:56,917 --> 00:31:57,960
I guess not.

429
00:31:59,294 --> 00:32:00,337
[PULSATING]

430
00:32:00,504 --> 00:32:01,547
JOE:
You see?

431
00:32:02,506 --> 00:32:05,801
You see? There it is again.

432
00:32:06,760 --> 00:32:09,721
That is not a transformer malfunction.

433
00:32:09,888 --> 00:32:11,974
That is an electromagnetic pulse.

434
00:32:12,808 --> 00:32:14,184
It affects everything electrical...

435
00:32:14,351 --> 00:32:15,727
...for miles and miles...

436
00:32:15,894 --> 00:32:17,729
...and it is happening again.

437
00:32:17,896 --> 00:32:20,315
This is what caused everything
in the first place.

438
00:32:20,482 --> 00:32:22,025
Don't you see that?

439
00:32:23,277 --> 00:32:25,737
And it is gonna send us
back to the Stone Age.

440
00:32:26,738 --> 00:32:28,949
You have no idea what's coming.

441
00:32:30,409 --> 00:32:32,202
[RUMBLING AND RATTLING]

442
00:32:33,829 --> 00:32:35,455
[ALARM BLARING]

443
00:32:35,622 --> 00:32:37,541
- Pulses are seconds apart.
- They're getting stronger.

444
00:32:37,708 --> 00:32:40,210
- It's affecting the power grid.
- Any radiation leakage?

445
00:32:40,377 --> 00:32:42,004
Gamma levels are still zero.

446
00:32:42,171 --> 00:32:43,839
It sucked all three reactors dry.

447
00:32:44,006 --> 00:32:45,966
[ENERG Y PULSATING]

448
00:32:53,015 --> 00:32:54,516
[SHOUTING IN JAPANESE]

449
00:32:55,726 --> 00:32:57,311
It's done feeding.

450
00:32:57,853 --> 00:32:58,937
What's this?

451
00:32:59,104 --> 00:33:01,148
- It's the same pattern.
SERIZAWA: Fifteen years ago...

452
00:33:01,315 --> 00:33:04,193
...it's what caused the meltdown.
GRAHAM: An electromagnetic...

453
00:33:04,359 --> 00:33:06,862
...pulse. That's what it's building to.
Converting all that radiation...

454
00:33:07,029 --> 00:33:08,780
...until it hatches.

455
00:33:08,947 --> 00:33:10,741
We have to shut down.

456
00:33:11,408 --> 00:33:12,493
WHELAN:
Secure the grid.

457
00:33:12,659 --> 00:33:13,911
Wildfire protocols.

458
00:33:15,287 --> 00:33:18,415
All personnel,
clear the first perimeter immediately!

459
00:33:28,634 --> 00:33:30,552
[MEN SPEAKING IN JAPANESE]

460
00:33:30,719 --> 00:33:33,055
FORD:
What's going on? Hey, where you going?

461
00:33:47,736 --> 00:33:48,779
[ALARM BLARES]

462
00:33:53,742 --> 00:33:54,785
Grid's secure.

463
00:34:03,460 --> 00:34:04,878
Kill it.

464
00:34:10,425 --> 00:34:12,177
[CRACKLING]

465
00:34:17,558 --> 00:34:19,351
[WHIRRING]

466
00:34:24,356 --> 00:34:26,149
[ALL YELLING]

467
00:34:36,910 --> 00:34:38,745
All readings are flatlined.

468
00:34:39,246 --> 00:34:40,581
Ahem.

469
00:34:41,165 --> 00:34:42,291
Get a visual.

470
00:34:59,433 --> 00:35:01,435
[RUMBLING]

471
00:35:10,402 --> 00:35:11,945
[MAN SCREAMS]

472
00:35:16,700 --> 00:35:19,536
WHELAN: Jesus. Check the grid. Hit us
with an EMP. We're losing power!

473
00:35:21,288 --> 00:35:23,290
[MAN SPEAKING IN JAPANESE
OVER PA]

474
00:35:32,883 --> 00:35:34,885
[MEN YELLING IN JAPANESE]

475
00:35:37,763 --> 00:35:40,182
WHELAN: Get the backup generators online.
MAN: Working on it.

476
00:35:40,349 --> 00:35:41,808
That pulse fried every circuit.

477
00:35:41,975 --> 00:35:44,353
- Check the cage.
MAN 2: Trying the backup generators.

478
00:35:44,520 --> 00:35:45,604
Here we go.

479
00:35:48,607 --> 00:35:49,900
[MUTO SHRIEKING]

480
00:35:57,991 --> 00:36:00,160
WHELAN:
Everybody out! Now!

481
00:36:00,327 --> 00:36:01,745
[ALL YELLING]

482
00:36:12,381 --> 00:36:13,674
[JOE GRUNTS]

483
00:36:28,814 --> 00:36:30,399
[SIRENS WAILING]

484
00:36:31,066 --> 00:36:33,694
Hey! Let me out! Hey!

485
00:36:38,699 --> 00:36:40,450
[MEN SPEAKING IN JAPANESE]

486
00:36:51,879 --> 00:36:53,881
[CREAKING]

487
00:37:05,392 --> 00:37:07,227
[ALL YELLING]

488
00:37:07,394 --> 00:37:09,396
JOE:
No! No, wait! Stop!

489
00:37:13,692 --> 00:37:15,027
[GRUNTING]

490
00:37:16,778 --> 00:37:17,821
Ford!

491
00:37:24,703 --> 00:37:26,163
[SCREAMING]

492
00:37:30,209 --> 00:37:31,251
[GRUNTS]

493
00:37:35,547 --> 00:37:36,590
Dad!

494
00:37:37,966 --> 00:37:39,676
[MUTO ROARING]

495
00:38:02,366 --> 00:38:03,826
[ALL YELLING]

496
00:38:14,545 --> 00:38:16,421
[BREATHING THROUGH MASK]

497
00:38:34,022 --> 00:38:37,234
<i>WOMAN [OVER TV]: It was unlike anything
I've ever experienced before.</i>

498
00:38:37,401 --> 00:38:39,236
ELLE:
Yeah, it's, uh, Ford Brody.

499
00:38:39,403 --> 00:38:41,405
Japan to San Francisco.

500
00:38:41,572 --> 00:38:44,408
Okay, could I at least...
If you could let me leave you my cell...

501
00:38:44,575 --> 00:38:45,617
[LINE CRACKLING]

502
00:38:45,784 --> 00:38:46,827
Hello?

503
00:38:46,994 --> 00:38:48,036
[BUS Y TONE]

504
00:38:48,203 --> 00:38:49,413
Damn it!

505
00:38:50,455 --> 00:38:51,874
[ELLE EXHALES]

506
00:38:57,754 --> 00:38:59,298
I'm sorry.

507
00:38:59,840 --> 00:39:01,842
Hey, it's okay.

508
00:39:02,217 --> 00:39:05,095
It's okay. Daddy's gonna be okay.

509
00:39:07,764 --> 00:39:09,391
Daddy's gonna be okay.

510
00:39:13,103 --> 00:39:16,565
<i>MAN [OVER PA]: This area is now under
Naval military jurisdiction.</i>

511
00:39:16,732 --> 00:39:18,233
<i>All personnel must report...</i>

512
00:39:18,400 --> 00:39:20,819
<i>... to the duty officer for debriefing.</i>

513
00:39:20,986 --> 00:39:23,489
[MAN SPEAKING IN JAPANESE
OVER PA]

514
00:39:28,785 --> 00:39:30,454
GRAHAM:
Dr. Serizawa!

515
00:39:32,789 --> 00:39:34,124
Dr. Serizawa!

516
00:39:34,583 --> 00:39:36,168
Dr. Serizawa.

517
00:39:36,335 --> 00:39:37,920
Captain Russell Hampton.

518
00:39:38,462 --> 00:39:39,880
Glad to find you. I've been briefed...

519
00:39:40,047 --> 00:39:41,882
...on your work with Operation Monarch.

520
00:39:42,049 --> 00:39:44,968
Now, I'm told your organization
has situational awareness...

521
00:39:45,135 --> 00:39:46,720
...of our unidentified creature?

522
00:39:47,304 --> 00:39:48,388
Is that right?

523
00:39:49,264 --> 00:39:51,975
We are now taking over
operational authority...

524
00:39:52,142 --> 00:39:54,144
...from Monarch. So I'm gonna need you...

525
00:39:54,311 --> 00:39:55,354
...to come with me.

526
00:39:55,521 --> 00:39:57,523
Is there any other personnel you need?

527
00:40:02,820 --> 00:40:04,112
FORD:
They'll take care of you.

528
00:40:04,279 --> 00:40:05,572
I'll be right next to you.

529
00:40:06,198 --> 00:40:07,282
Okay.

530
00:40:09,701 --> 00:40:10,744
Them.

531
00:40:30,639 --> 00:40:32,766
MAN: Let's get his vitals.
FORD: Shh. Shh.

532
00:40:32,933 --> 00:40:36,186
- Dad. Dad.
MAN: Radial pulse is weak. I'm counting 125.

533
00:40:37,062 --> 00:40:38,397
FORD:
It's okay.

534
00:40:43,277 --> 00:40:44,528
You were right.

535
00:40:48,240 --> 00:40:49,533
I'm sorry.

536
00:40:52,202 --> 00:40:53,954
Go home to your family.

537
00:40:54,663 --> 00:40:56,999
You keep them safe.

538
00:40:58,959 --> 00:41:00,669
JOE: Okay?
- Okay.

539
00:41:02,713 --> 00:41:04,256
Whatever it takes.

540
00:41:05,591 --> 00:41:06,800
Whatever it ta...

541
00:41:08,093 --> 00:41:09,845
FORD:
Hey, stay with me.

542
00:41:10,012 --> 00:41:11,054
Dad?

543
00:41:11,221 --> 00:41:13,307
- Dad?
MAN: Radial pulse is weaker. Barely feel it.

544
00:41:13,473 --> 00:41:14,516
We're losing him.

545
00:41:14,683 --> 00:41:16,894
- Joe, can you hear me?
MAN 2: He's going into A-fib.

546
00:41:17,060 --> 00:41:20,397
Give me another epi, one milligram,
and 40 units of vasopressin.

547
00:41:20,564 --> 00:41:23,066
Stay with us. Come on, Joe.
Hang in there, buddy.

548
00:41:30,657 --> 00:41:32,743
STENZ:
This is our needle in a haystack, people.

549
00:41:33,243 --> 00:41:34,453
MUTO.

550
00:41:34,620 --> 00:41:37,414
Massive unidentified terrestrial organism.

551
00:41:37,581 --> 00:41:41,168
It is, however, no longer terrestrial.
It is airborne.

552
00:41:41,335 --> 00:41:43,545
The world still thinks
this was an earthquake...

553
00:41:43,712 --> 00:41:46,048
...and it would be preferable that
that remain so.

554
00:41:47,758 --> 00:41:50,469
Before we lost sight, it was
headed east across the Pacific...

555
00:41:50,636 --> 00:41:52,679
...and had emitted enough
EMP disruption...

556
00:41:52,846 --> 00:41:55,516
...to create havoc with
our radar and satellite feeds...

557
00:41:55,682 --> 00:41:59,603
...and reduce us, for the moment,
to a strictly visual pursuit.

558
00:41:59,770 --> 00:42:01,772
I emphasize "for the moment"...

559
00:42:01,939 --> 00:42:04,107
...because we will get on our game...

560
00:42:04,274 --> 00:42:06,193
...and we will find this thing.

561
00:42:07,361 --> 00:42:10,030
It is imperative that we do so.

562
00:42:11,114 --> 00:42:12,199
Captain, I want any...

563
00:42:12,366 --> 00:42:15,577
...and all search options on this table ASAP.
- Yes, sir.

564
00:42:20,499 --> 00:42:22,125
STENZ:
Dr. Serizawa.

565
00:42:22,501 --> 00:42:23,544
Admiral William Stenz.

566
00:42:26,046 --> 00:42:28,298
SERIZAWA: Nice to meet you.
- Glad to have you on board.

567
00:42:28,465 --> 00:42:29,675
GRAHAM:
Sensei.

568
00:42:32,094 --> 00:42:33,262
SERIZAWA:
Excuse me.

569
00:42:34,721 --> 00:42:37,015
<i>MAN [ON TV]: Authorities made a statement...
GRAHAM: Brody's dead.</i>

570
00:42:37,182 --> 00:42:38,767
<i>... claiming the nuclear contamination...</i>

571
00:42:38,934 --> 00:42:42,938
<i>... is at no risk of spreading,
even as the death toll rises.</i>

572
00:43:02,791 --> 00:43:03,917
[KNOCKING]

573
00:43:04,084 --> 00:43:05,669
Lieutenant Brody?

574
00:43:08,589 --> 00:43:10,215
MAN:
Dr. Serizawa.

575
00:43:14,094 --> 00:43:15,679
My condolences.

576
00:43:16,388 --> 00:43:18,849
We are deeply sorry for your loss,
lieutenant.

577
00:43:20,017 --> 00:43:21,977
But I'm afraid we need your help.

578
00:43:24,897 --> 00:43:27,941
<i>MAN [ON FILM]: This is the USS Nautilus.
SERIZAWA: In 1954...</i>

579
00:43:28,442 --> 00:43:32,279
...the first time a nuclear submarine
ever reached the lower depths...

580
00:43:33,280 --> 00:43:35,532
...it awakened something.
GRAHAM: The Americans...

581
00:43:35,699 --> 00:43:37,951
...first thought that it was the Russians.

582
00:43:38,118 --> 00:43:40,162
The Russians thought that it was them.

583
00:43:40,871 --> 00:43:43,123
All those nuclear bomb tests
in the '50s?

584
00:43:46,418 --> 00:43:47,461
Not tests.

585
00:43:48,795 --> 00:43:50,506
SERIZAWA:
They were trying to kill it.

586
00:43:52,174 --> 00:43:53,217
Him.

587
00:43:54,968 --> 00:43:57,888
- An ancient alpha predator.
GRAHAM: Millions of years...

588
00:43:58,055 --> 00:43:59,431
...older than mankind.

589
00:43:59,598 --> 00:44:00,807
From an age when the Earth...

590
00:44:00,974 --> 00:44:02,851
...was 10 times more radioactive
than today.

591
00:44:04,811 --> 00:44:06,813
This animal and others like it...

592
00:44:06,980 --> 00:44:09,650
...consumed this radiation as a food source.

593
00:44:09,817 --> 00:44:12,194
As the levels on the surface
naturally subsided...

594
00:44:12,361 --> 00:44:14,613
...these creatures adapted
to live deeper in the oceans.

595
00:44:15,197 --> 00:44:16,657
Further underground.

596
00:44:17,157 --> 00:44:19,660
Absorbing radiation
from the planet's core.

597
00:44:20,118 --> 00:44:23,330
The organization we work for, Monarch,
was established...

598
00:44:23,497 --> 00:44:25,290
...in the wake of this discovery.

599
00:44:25,916 --> 00:44:27,501
A multinational coalition...

600
00:44:27,668 --> 00:44:29,044
...formed in secrecy...

601
00:44:29,837 --> 00:44:31,296
...to search for him.

602
00:44:31,463 --> 00:44:32,965
Study him.

603
00:44:33,298 --> 00:44:35,050
Learn everything we could.

604
00:44:35,843 --> 00:44:37,010
We call him...

605
00:44:39,012 --> 00:44:40,138
<i>... Gojira.</i>

606
00:44:40,305 --> 00:44:41,348
GRAHAM:
The top of...

607
00:44:41,515 --> 00:44:43,267
...a primordial ecosystem.

608
00:44:44,309 --> 00:44:47,437
A god, for all intents and purposes.

609
00:44:48,355 --> 00:44:50,691
- A monster.
SERIZAWA: Fifteen years ago...

610
00:44:50,858 --> 00:44:54,486
...we found a fossil of another giant animal
in the Philippines.

611
00:44:54,653 --> 00:44:57,698
<i>Like Gojira. But this creature...</i>

612
00:44:57,865 --> 00:44:59,158
...died long ago.

613
00:44:59,324 --> 00:45:01,160
Killed by these.

614
00:45:01,660 --> 00:45:02,995
GRAHAM:
Parasitic spores.

615
00:45:03,579 --> 00:45:07,040
One dormant. But the other hatched.
Catalyzed when a mining company...

616
00:45:07,207 --> 00:45:09,334
...unknowingly drilled into its tomb.

617
00:45:09,668 --> 00:45:12,504
The hatchling burrowed straight for
the nearest source of radiation...

618
00:45:12,671 --> 00:45:15,299
...your father's power plant in Janjira...

619
00:45:15,465 --> 00:45:18,302
...and cocooned there for 15 years,
absorbing its radioactive fuel...

620
00:45:18,468 --> 00:45:21,305
...to gestate, to grow.
SERIZAWA: Until it hatched...

621
00:45:21,471 --> 00:45:23,974
...like a butterfly into the creature
you saw today.

622
00:45:24,141 --> 00:45:26,018
Wait. You knew about this?

623
00:45:26,185 --> 00:45:29,396
This thing? The whole time?
Why didn't you...

624
00:45:29,563 --> 00:45:31,482
...kill it when you had the chance?
GRAHAM: It was absorbing...

625
00:45:31,648 --> 00:45:33,901
...radiation from the reactors.

626
00:45:34,067 --> 00:45:35,235
We worried killing it...

627
00:45:35,402 --> 00:45:38,405
...might release that radiation
and endanger millions.

628
00:45:38,572 --> 00:45:41,074
SERIZAWA:
That's why our mission was to contain it.

629
00:45:41,241 --> 00:45:44,203
To study its biology, to understand it.

630
00:45:44,786 --> 00:45:46,663
GRAHAM: We knew the creature
was having an electrical effect...

631
00:45:46,830 --> 00:45:48,957
...on everything within a close proximity.

632
00:45:49,124 --> 00:45:50,167
What we didn't know...

633
00:45:50,334 --> 00:45:52,753
...was that it could harness
this same power...

634
00:45:52,920 --> 00:45:55,047
...in an EMP attack.

635
00:45:55,923 --> 00:45:57,382
But your father did.

636
00:45:58,091 --> 00:45:59,510
He predicted it.

637
00:45:59,676 --> 00:46:01,595
SERIZAWA:
What else did he say?

638
00:46:01,970 --> 00:46:04,264
GRAHAM:
Please try to remember, Mr. Brody.

639
00:46:04,431 --> 00:46:07,851
Anything that would help us.
Anything at all.

640
00:46:08,018 --> 00:46:09,520
I didn't listen.

641
00:46:10,270 --> 00:46:12,105
I just thought he was crazy.

642
00:46:12,940 --> 00:46:15,025
He was obsessed with all this...

643
00:46:15,192 --> 00:46:16,652
[SIGHS]

644
00:46:18,237 --> 00:46:20,781
Said something about an animal call.

645
00:46:23,200 --> 00:46:24,618
Something talking.

646
00:46:25,244 --> 00:46:26,286
SERIZAWA:
Talking?

647
00:46:27,162 --> 00:46:28,956
FORD:
He said he was studying something.

648
00:46:29,498 --> 00:46:30,999
Echolocation.

649
00:46:31,834 --> 00:46:34,253
If the MUTO was talking that day...

650
00:46:34,920 --> 00:46:38,173
...your father must have discovered
something talking back.

651
00:46:39,466 --> 00:46:40,759
- Check again.
- Yup.

652
00:46:41,134 --> 00:46:42,594
Search for a response call.

653
00:46:42,761 --> 00:46:44,429
FORD:
This parasite.

654
00:46:44,805 --> 00:46:48,308
It's still out there. Where's it headed?

655
00:46:48,475 --> 00:46:50,143
SERIZAWA:
The MUTO is young...

656
00:46:50,310 --> 00:46:51,353
...growing.

657
00:46:52,771 --> 00:46:54,189
It will be looking for food.

658
00:46:54,898 --> 00:46:56,650
Sources of radiation.

659
00:46:56,817 --> 00:46:59,069
We're monitoring all known sites...

660
00:46:59,945 --> 00:47:01,029
...but if we don't find it soon...

661
00:47:01,738 --> 00:47:03,031
Then what?

662
00:47:04,199 --> 00:47:05,742
Nature has an order.

663
00:47:06,702 --> 00:47:08,162
A power to restore balance.

664
00:47:09,371 --> 00:47:12,499
I believe he is that power.

665
00:47:16,461 --> 00:47:19,214
MAN:
Sir, right now we're 50 miles from Hawaii.

666
00:47:19,381 --> 00:47:21,675
This transport will take you there.

667
00:47:22,301 --> 00:47:26,013
You're catching a commercial flight
back to San Francisco.

668
00:47:39,109 --> 00:47:41,320
ELLE:
I'm gonna need you to brush your teeth.

669
00:47:41,862 --> 00:47:44,740
- Disgusting! Those are terrible!
SAM: Ha, ha.

670
00:47:44,907 --> 00:47:46,033
ELLE:
We gotta brush them!

671
00:47:46,200 --> 00:47:48,035
<i>WOMAN [OVER TV]:
Citizens within a 100-mile radius...</i>

672
00:47:48,202 --> 00:47:50,204
<i>... are being temporarily evacuated
from the area.</i>

673
00:47:50,370 --> 00:47:51,747
[PHONE VIBRATING]

674
00:47:51,914 --> 00:47:54,875
<i>[RECORDING] Hey, this is Elle.
You missed me. Please leave a message.</i>

675
00:47:55,459 --> 00:47:56,627
Elle.

676
00:47:58,754 --> 00:48:01,840
I don't know what they're saying
on the news.

677
00:48:02,007 --> 00:48:04,301
There was an accident in Japan.

678
00:48:06,428 --> 00:48:07,763
Dad's gone.

679
00:48:08,764 --> 00:48:10,641
I'll explain when I see you.

680
00:48:11,350 --> 00:48:14,353
I'm headed to Hawaii.
I'm gonna catch a flight from there.

681
00:48:14,895 --> 00:48:16,438
I'll see you soon.

682
00:48:18,649 --> 00:48:20,651
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

683
00:48:25,989 --> 00:48:27,366
GRAHAM:
Keep scrolling.

684
00:48:28,325 --> 00:48:30,661
Near the end. Before the EMP.

685
00:48:32,204 --> 00:48:33,247
[COMPUTER BEEPS]

686
00:48:33,413 --> 00:48:34,456
There.

687
00:48:36,875 --> 00:48:38,627
Something responded.

688
00:48:47,511 --> 00:48:49,513
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

689
00:48:51,056 --> 00:48:53,642
<i>MAN [OVER PA]:
Aloha, and welcome aboard.</i>

690
00:48:53,809 --> 00:48:56,103
<i>The train will begin moving shortly.</i>

691
00:48:56,270 --> 00:48:59,565
<i>For the comfort of others,
no smoking, please. Thank you.</i>

692
00:49:03,777 --> 00:49:06,530
<i>Please remember to stay clear
of the automatic doors.</i>

693
00:49:06,697 --> 00:49:07,865
MAN:
Akio!

694
00:49:08,031 --> 00:49:09,408
AKIO:
Mama!

695
00:49:09,575 --> 00:49:10,951
Mama!

696
00:49:11,869 --> 00:49:12,911
FORD:
Hey, hey, hey.

697
00:49:14,079 --> 00:49:15,539
- Mama!
- I can't open it.

698
00:49:15,706 --> 00:49:17,749
Look, don't worry. Just wait there.

699
00:49:17,916 --> 00:49:19,668
I'll bring him back. Okay?

700
00:49:19,835 --> 00:49:20,878
AKIO: Mama!
FORD: Hey, hey.

701
00:49:21,044 --> 00:49:22,254
AKIO:
Mama!

702
00:49:22,421 --> 00:49:24,256
[FORD SPEAKS IN JAPANESE]

703
00:49:24,423 --> 00:49:26,258
FORD: Whoa. Hey. Whoa, kid.
AKIO: Mama!

704
00:49:26,425 --> 00:49:28,385
FORD:
It's okay. I'm gonna bring him back.

705
00:49:29,469 --> 00:49:31,597
All right. I'm gonna set you down there.

706
00:49:31,763 --> 00:49:33,015
I'll get you back to your parents.

707
00:49:33,182 --> 00:49:34,224
Okay?

708
00:49:34,933 --> 00:49:36,018
Here. Is this what you want?

709
00:49:37,352 --> 00:49:39,354
Take good care of him for me.

710
00:49:40,105 --> 00:49:42,733
I better not miss my flight, kid.

711
00:49:43,692 --> 00:49:45,819
MAN:
Admiral, received an intel report.

712
00:49:45,986 --> 00:49:49,156
We lost track of a nuclear Akula
50 nautical miles northwest of Hawaii.

713
00:49:49,323 --> 00:49:50,657
Could be the MUTO.

714
00:49:54,828 --> 00:49:57,998
Just got word of a missing Russian sub
in the North Pacific.

715
00:49:58,999 --> 00:50:00,042
Martinez?

716
00:50:00,209 --> 00:50:03,170
Aye. Special Forces Team Sparta 1
is picking up a distress signal...

717
00:50:03,337 --> 00:50:05,380
...northwest of Diamond Head
on the island of Oahu.

718
00:50:05,547 --> 00:50:07,424
They're on the ground,
headed to the beacon.

719
00:50:07,591 --> 00:50:09,593
<i>MAN [OVER RADIO]:
- on 5.23 north-northeast...</i>

720
00:50:09,760 --> 00:50:12,095
<i>... of the last beacon. Moving in on foot.</i>

721
00:50:26,568 --> 00:50:28,195
MAN:
Wanna tell me why we're looking...

722
00:50:28,362 --> 00:50:29,863
...for an Akula in the jungle?

723
00:50:30,030 --> 00:50:32,032
MAN 2:
Probably a glitch. Russians said they...

724
00:50:32,199 --> 00:50:33,617
...got a ping from this location.

725
00:50:33,784 --> 00:50:35,994
MAN 3:
Hey, I got a reading. It's right up ahead.

726
00:50:36,161 --> 00:50:38,080
[HELICOPTER WHIRRING]

727
00:50:39,748 --> 00:50:41,041
<i>PILOT:
Sparta 1, this is Hawkeye.</i>

728
00:50:41,208 --> 00:50:44,586
<i>We're getting the same ping off
the transponder. Range 30 meters.</i>

729
00:50:44,753 --> 00:50:46,421
<i>Looks like you're getting warm.</i>

730
00:50:47,548 --> 00:50:49,508
[TRACKER BEEPING]

731
00:50:49,675 --> 00:50:51,134
MAN:
What the hell?

732
00:50:51,301 --> 00:50:52,886
[BEEPING INCREASES]

733
00:51:01,436 --> 00:51:03,021
Jesus.

734
00:51:07,401 --> 00:51:08,986
Oh, my God.

735
00:51:21,165 --> 00:51:22,958
Guardian 3, we located your Russian sub.

736
00:51:23,709 --> 00:51:25,669
<i>You're not gonna believe
what else we found.</i>

737
00:51:25,836 --> 00:51:26,879
Holy shit.

738
00:51:33,886 --> 00:51:36,847
<i>MAN [OVER RADIO]: It appears to be rising
approximately 20 to 30 meters...</i>

739
00:51:37,014 --> 00:51:38,098
<i>... above the tree line.</i>

740
00:51:38,265 --> 00:51:39,933
<i>We can't tell how wide it is.</i>

741
00:51:40,100 --> 00:51:42,853
Cat's out of the bag, doctor.
No more secrets.

742
00:51:43,020 --> 00:51:45,272
Our highest priority now is safety.

743
00:51:45,439 --> 00:51:47,941
There's close to a million people
on that island.

744
00:51:48,775 --> 00:51:49,860
Get me eyes in the air.

745
00:51:50,027 --> 00:51:53,197
MAN: We're picking up something else.
Approaching from the Pacific.

746
00:51:53,363 --> 00:51:55,324
STENZ:
We need to check out that object.

747
00:51:55,491 --> 00:51:56,783
General quarters.

748
00:51:56,950 --> 00:51:57,993
[BOSUN WHISTLE]

749
00:51:58,160 --> 00:51:59,786
Bridge, this is the captain.

750
00:51:59,953 --> 00:52:02,080
- Where you going?
- Up to the flight deck.

751
00:52:02,247 --> 00:52:03,665
I think he is coming.

752
00:52:03,832 --> 00:52:05,083
What are you doing?

753
00:52:05,250 --> 00:52:06,919
I have to see this.

754
00:52:17,513 --> 00:52:19,890
[HAWAIIAN MUSIC PLAYING
OVER SPEAKER]

755
00:52:22,392 --> 00:52:24,394
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

756
00:52:41,203 --> 00:52:42,663
[ALL YELLING]

757
00:53:02,683 --> 00:53:04,226
AKIO:
Whoa.

758
00:53:04,601 --> 00:53:08,313
Two Charlie Six, we are circling the target.
Go on your command.

759
00:53:08,772 --> 00:53:11,441
Stand by, got a visual. Bogey at my 12.

760
00:53:12,776 --> 00:53:14,653
[MUTO SNARLS]

761
00:53:20,576 --> 00:53:23,287
Be advised. Prepare to engage target.

762
00:53:23,453 --> 00:53:25,497
We're getting movement down here.

763
00:53:27,875 --> 00:53:29,585
[SHRIEKING]

764
00:53:29,751 --> 00:53:30,794
MAN 2:
Take cover!

765
00:53:32,421 --> 00:53:33,589
[ALL YELLING]

766
00:53:37,676 --> 00:53:38,719
Control, I have...

767
00:53:38,886 --> 00:53:40,637
...no power. I say again, I've lost all...

768
00:53:43,140 --> 00:53:44,558
[SCREAMING]

769
00:53:48,395 --> 00:53:49,480
[ALL YELL]

770
00:53:51,899 --> 00:53:53,192
FORD:
You all right?

771
00:53:54,401 --> 00:53:56,737
You give it 10 seconds,
lights gonna come back on.

772
00:53:57,738 --> 00:53:59,114
It's okay.

773
00:54:03,744 --> 00:54:06,038
WOMAN: What was that?
MAN: Did you see that?

774
00:54:12,252 --> 00:54:13,712
MAN 2:
What is it?

775
00:54:21,720 --> 00:54:22,763
Dad!

776
00:54:23,680 --> 00:54:24,765
Zoe?

777
00:54:25,474 --> 00:54:26,558
Zoe!

778
00:54:27,809 --> 00:54:29,186
Oh, my God.

779
00:54:30,771 --> 00:54:31,814
[ALARM BLARING]

780
00:54:31,980 --> 00:54:34,024
Run. Run! Tsunami! Tsunami!

781
00:54:34,191 --> 00:54:36,151
[ALL YELLING]

782
00:54:38,320 --> 00:54:40,197
<i>PILOT [OVER RADIO]:
Target spotted offshore...</i>

783
00:54:40,364 --> 00:54:42,741
...two knots due east of your position.
Could be a second bogey.

784
00:54:46,537 --> 00:54:48,747
[MEN SHOUTING INDISTINCTLY]

785
00:55:30,664 --> 00:55:33,250
[WHINING AND BARKING]

786
00:55:46,597 --> 00:55:47,973
[ALL SCREAMING]

787
00:56:49,618 --> 00:56:51,078
[ALL SCREAMING]

788
00:57:04,800 --> 00:57:06,134
SERGEANT:
Anybody hurt?

789
00:57:06,301 --> 00:57:08,637
- Anyone get an eyeball on the bogey?
MAN: Where is he?

790
00:57:08,804 --> 00:57:10,597
[SNARLING]

791
00:57:25,988 --> 00:57:27,030
FORD:
There you go.

792
00:57:27,197 --> 00:57:28,448
What did I tell you?

793
00:57:31,076 --> 00:57:32,703
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

794
00:57:36,039 --> 00:57:38,083
<i>MAN [OVER PA]:
- please. Thank you.</i>

795
00:57:38,917 --> 00:57:40,460
[ROARING]

796
00:57:40,627 --> 00:57:42,462
[CROWD SHOUTING]

797
00:57:51,013 --> 00:57:52,055
[GUNFIRE]

798
00:57:52,222 --> 00:57:53,682
Get down!

799
00:57:53,849 --> 00:57:55,058
[ALL YELLING]

800
00:58:02,941 --> 00:58:05,152
[ROARING]

801
00:58:05,319 --> 00:58:06,904
- Aah!
- Let's go!

802
00:58:11,658 --> 00:58:13,243
[ALL SCREAMING]

803
00:58:19,082 --> 00:58:20,417
<i>MAN [OVER PA]:
Remember to stay...</i>

804
00:58:20,584 --> 00:58:21,627
<i>... clear of the doors.</i>

805
00:58:24,963 --> 00:58:26,381
MAN:
Go, go, go!

806
00:58:35,974 --> 00:58:37,267
[MUTO ROARING]

807
00:58:37,434 --> 00:58:38,769
<i>PILOT [OVER RADIO]:
Target in sight...</i>

808
00:58:38,936 --> 00:58:42,314
...two o'clock, 300 meters.
- We're on 6-X-01. Target confirmed.

809
00:58:45,567 --> 00:58:46,610
Jesus!

810
00:58:48,904 --> 00:58:50,072
[GROWLING]

811
00:58:53,826 --> 00:58:55,494
[ALL SCREAMING]

812
00:59:11,885 --> 00:59:13,220
[SNARLS]

813
00:59:21,812 --> 00:59:24,231
[SHRIEKING]

814
00:59:28,986 --> 00:59:30,988
[POP MUSIC PLAYING
OVER SPEAKERS]

815
00:59:31,613 --> 00:59:33,866
<i>MAN [OVER TV]:
Can you tell us what happened?</i>

816
00:59:34,408 --> 00:59:37,828
<i>WOMAN: ... and everybody started running
and screaming.</i>

817
00:59:38,829 --> 00:59:41,039
Sam, please turn that TV off.

818
00:59:43,250 --> 00:59:44,668
[ELLE SIGHS]

819
00:59:47,379 --> 00:59:49,089
Hey, did you hear me?

820
00:59:49,256 --> 00:59:50,382
Off.

821
00:59:55,262 --> 00:59:56,430
Come on, Sammy. Let's go.

822
00:59:57,014 --> 00:59:58,390
Let's go. It's bedtime.

823
00:59:58,974 --> 01:00:01,268
- Sammy.
- Mommy, look.

824
01:00:01,435 --> 01:00:03,270
Dinosaurs.

825
01:00:07,900 --> 01:00:09,401
[BIRDS SQUAWKING]

826
01:00:16,575 --> 01:00:18,577
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

827
01:00:22,122 --> 01:00:24,791
<i>MAN [OVER PA]:
Attention, please. Incoming patients...</i>

828
01:00:24,958 --> 01:00:27,461
<i>...please proceed...
FORD: Excuse me.</i>

829
01:00:27,628 --> 01:00:29,129
Hi. Excuse me. I'm sorry.

830
01:00:29,296 --> 01:00:31,298
This boy's been separated from his parents.

831
01:00:31,465 --> 01:00:32,508
Fill this out. Be with you...

832
01:00:32,674 --> 01:00:33,926
...in just a minute.

833
01:00:35,010 --> 01:00:36,887
FORD:
Hey, you got service on that cell phone?

834
01:00:37,054 --> 01:00:38,847
No. The pay phones don't even work.

835
01:00:49,983 --> 01:00:52,319
WOMAN: Akio!
MAN: Akio!

836
01:00:52,736 --> 01:00:54,238
AKIO:
Mama! Papa!

837
01:00:59,660 --> 01:01:01,411
MAN:
Corporal, load up, load up.

838
01:01:03,747 --> 01:01:05,874
Sergeant. Lieutenant Brody, U.S. Navy.

839
01:01:06,041 --> 01:01:08,502
I need your help.
I'm trying to get to the mainland.

840
01:01:08,669 --> 01:01:11,421
It's your lucky day.
Everything not tied down is moving east.

841
01:01:11,588 --> 01:01:13,757
- Whoa, is that where they're heading?
- Yeah.

842
01:01:14,424 --> 01:01:16,301
I guess we're monster hunters now.

843
01:01:36,947 --> 01:01:38,115
<i>WOMAN:
Satellite transfer complete.</i>

844
01:01:39,616 --> 01:01:41,368
Simulations uploaded.

845
01:01:41,535 --> 01:01:43,078
Satellite tracking continues.

846
01:01:43,245 --> 01:01:46,039
Last satellite tracks predict
the MUTO continuing due east.

847
01:01:46,206 --> 01:01:48,584
All our models have the targets
converging on the Pacific Coast.

848
01:01:48,750 --> 01:01:51,044
As of now, it looks like Godzilla's
still following the MUTO.

849
01:01:51,211 --> 01:01:52,462
He's hunting.

850
01:01:54,131 --> 01:01:56,675
Have all vessels maintain
current distance from target.

851
01:01:56,842 --> 01:01:59,178
And plot the speed and heading
of these things.

852
01:01:59,344 --> 01:02:02,014
I wanna know exactly when and where
they'll make landfall.

853
01:02:02,181 --> 01:02:03,515
MAN:
Yes, sir.

854
01:02:03,682 --> 01:02:05,601
Doctor, what did you mean by "hunting"?

855
01:02:06,310 --> 01:02:08,520
You think it's chasing this MUTO?

856
01:02:08,687 --> 01:02:10,564
But if the MUTO is his prey...

857
01:02:10,731 --> 01:02:12,316
The signal shows a call.

858
01:02:12,483 --> 01:02:14,568
- Why call up a predator?
SERIZAWA: No, it didn't.

859
01:02:14,735 --> 01:02:15,777
I think Godzilla...

860
01:02:15,944 --> 01:02:17,237
...was only listening.

861
01:02:17,863 --> 01:02:20,365
The MUTO was calling something else.

862
01:02:27,206 --> 01:02:28,499
The pattern.

863
01:02:29,458 --> 01:02:31,126
Focus the search on Nevada.

864
01:02:31,293 --> 01:02:33,212
Nevada? Why would it go to Nevada?

865
01:02:33,378 --> 01:02:36,131
- It can't be. It's impossible.
- What's impossible?

866
01:02:36,298 --> 01:02:40,177
There was another spore, intact,
found in the Philippine mine.

867
01:02:40,844 --> 01:02:42,471
But we vivisected it.

868
01:02:42,638 --> 01:02:44,515
Ran every test on it for years.

869
01:02:44,681 --> 01:02:47,518
You confirmed it for yourself.
It was dormant!

870
01:02:47,684 --> 01:02:49,353
Maybe not anymore.

871
01:02:49,520 --> 01:02:51,772
This spore. Where is it now, doctor?

872
01:02:51,939 --> 01:02:54,775
It was highly radioactive.
It was disposed of.

873
01:02:54,942 --> 01:02:56,443
The Americans, they took it.

874
01:02:56,610 --> 01:02:58,195
STENZ:
Doctor, where is it?

875
01:02:59,822 --> 01:03:02,491
Where you put all your nuclear waste.

876
01:03:25,556 --> 01:03:27,057
Go, go, go!

877
01:03:34,439 --> 01:03:36,275
MAN:
Right, let's go! Give me a Mark I...

878
01:03:36,441 --> 01:03:37,484
...eyeball on every vault.

879
01:03:41,155 --> 01:03:42,197
MAN 2:
Clear!

880
01:03:42,990 --> 01:03:44,032
MAN 3:
Clear!

881
01:03:46,451 --> 01:03:47,494
Clear!

882
01:03:47,661 --> 01:03:49,121
MAN 4: Clear!
MAN 5: Clear!

883
01:03:49,413 --> 01:03:50,455
MAN 6:
Clear!

884
01:03:51,081 --> 01:03:53,083
MAN 7: Clear!
MAN 8: Clear!

885
01:03:54,084 --> 01:03:55,127
Hey!

886
01:04:19,568 --> 01:04:21,570
[MUTO SHRIEKING]

887
01:04:23,614 --> 01:04:25,616
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

888
01:04:35,918 --> 01:04:37,920
[ALL CLAMORING]

889
01:04:40,839 --> 01:04:43,258
[CROWD SCREAMING
AND MUTO GROWLING]

890
01:04:43,967 --> 01:04:46,053
[ELVIS PRESLEY MUSIC
PLAYING OVER SPEAKER]

891
01:04:46,220 --> 01:04:49,056
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

892
01:04:49,223 --> 01:04:50,766
MAN:
Is anyone in there?

893
01:04:50,933 --> 01:04:52,518
[BANGING ON DOOR]

894
01:05:14,832 --> 01:05:17,000
<i>MAN: Captain, our UAVs have footage
of the new MUTO.</i>

895
01:05:17,167 --> 01:05:18,210
<i>STENZ:
Let's have a look.</i>

896
01:05:18,377 --> 01:05:19,419
MAN:
Yes, sir.

897
01:05:21,672 --> 01:05:23,215
This is from five minutes ago.

898
01:05:23,382 --> 01:05:24,758
STENZ:
My God.

899
01:05:28,470 --> 01:05:29,805
MAN:
Playing all we have now.

900
01:05:31,348 --> 01:05:32,724
It's almost 300 feet.

901
01:05:33,267 --> 01:05:34,935
It's far bigger than the other one.

902
01:05:35,561 --> 01:05:37,229
But this one doesn't have any wings.

903
01:05:38,689 --> 01:05:40,190
A different sex?

904
01:05:41,316 --> 01:05:42,526
A female.

905
01:05:44,987 --> 01:05:46,738
GRAHAM:
That's who he's been talking to.

906
01:05:47,156 --> 01:05:48,782
SERIZAWA:
It must be a mating call.

907
01:05:48,949 --> 01:05:51,618
The female remained dormant
until the male matured.

908
01:05:52,494 --> 01:05:54,079
GRAHAM:
Now they're seeking radiation.

909
01:05:55,414 --> 01:05:56,915
To reproduce.

910
01:05:59,251 --> 01:06:02,796
Current tracking models indicate that
all three targets are converging here:

911
01:06:02,963 --> 01:06:04,006
San Francisco Bay.

912
01:06:04,381 --> 01:06:07,467
But if we rig a nuclear warhead
with a shielded timer...

913
01:06:07,926 --> 01:06:09,094
...put it on a boat and send it...

914
01:06:09,261 --> 01:06:10,304
...20 miles out...

915
01:06:10,470 --> 01:06:12,306
...the radiation lures the MUTOs...

916
01:06:12,931 --> 01:06:14,683
...and the MUTOs lure Godzilla.

917
01:06:14,850 --> 01:06:17,936
And we detonate,
with minimal fallout risk to the city.

918
01:06:18,103 --> 01:06:20,939
You can't be serious.
They feed on radiation.

919
01:06:21,106 --> 01:06:23,650
Correct. That's why we use
the bomb as bait.

920
01:06:23,817 --> 01:06:24,985
MAN:
And kill them...

921
01:06:25,152 --> 01:06:28,113
...with the sheer force of the blast.
GRAHAM: This is crazy.

922
01:06:28,614 --> 01:06:31,492
Doctor, if you have any other ideas,
I am all ears.

923
01:06:31,658 --> 01:06:32,910
SERIZAWA:
Admiral.

924
01:06:34,703 --> 01:06:35,996
STENZ:
Yes, doctor?

925
01:06:37,581 --> 01:06:39,082
<i>Gojira may be the answer.</i>

926
01:06:39,374 --> 01:06:40,417
I believe...

927
01:06:40,584 --> 01:06:43,045
...he's here to restore balance.

928
01:06:43,629 --> 01:06:45,172
He can defeat them.

929
01:06:45,339 --> 01:06:47,966
STENZ:
And what? We just stand by and watch?

930
01:06:48,133 --> 01:06:51,094
I'm sorry, doctor. I can't take that risk.

931
01:06:53,013 --> 01:06:54,890
Prep the warheads
and get them moving to the coast.

932
01:06:55,057 --> 01:06:56,683
CAPTAIN: Yes, sir.
MAN: Yes, sir.

933
01:07:08,904 --> 01:07:10,322
I know you don't agree with this.

934
01:07:11,031 --> 01:07:14,409
But my first priority
is to safeguard our citizens.

935
01:07:24,711 --> 01:07:26,046
It's stopped.

936
01:07:26,213 --> 01:07:27,256
Yes.

937
01:07:28,215 --> 01:07:29,591
Eight-fifteen in the morning.

938
01:07:29,758 --> 01:07:32,928
August 6, 1945.

939
01:07:35,848 --> 01:07:37,224
Hiroshima.

940
01:07:38,809 --> 01:07:40,352
It was my father's.

941
01:07:53,407 --> 01:07:54,449
MAN:
Heads up.

942
01:07:54,616 --> 01:07:56,618
We've got new destination, new orders.

943
01:07:56,785 --> 01:07:57,828
Let's get geared up.

944
01:07:57,995 --> 01:07:59,079
FORD:
Hey, tech sergeant.

945
01:07:59,246 --> 01:08:00,289
What's the word?

946
01:08:01,373 --> 01:08:04,001
Another one of those things
popped up in Nevada, sir.

947
01:08:05,586 --> 01:08:07,004
[SIGHS]

948
01:08:16,346 --> 01:08:18,348
[MAN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY
OVER PA]

949
01:08:32,946 --> 01:08:34,781
MAN:
Okay, everybody out.

950
01:08:35,407 --> 01:08:37,159
Can't fly any further.

951
01:08:37,659 --> 01:08:39,495
We're well in range of its EMP.

952
01:08:39,661 --> 01:08:43,290
So from here on out, it's on the ground
or it's not at all. Let's go!

953
01:08:43,457 --> 01:08:45,501
[TRAIN HORN BLOWING]

954
01:08:53,634 --> 01:08:54,801
MAN:
All right, listen up!

955
01:08:54,968 --> 01:08:58,388
This train and these weapons
are headed to San Francisco.

956
01:08:58,555 --> 01:09:01,099
Anyone not part of this mission,
disembark now!

957
01:09:05,187 --> 01:09:06,355
<i>MAN 2:
Negative.</i>

958
01:09:06,522 --> 01:09:07,564
Can't do it, sir.

959
01:09:07,731 --> 01:09:11,443
This is a high-risk mission.
That train is a national asset, not Amtrak.

960
01:09:11,610 --> 01:09:12,986
- We good to go?
- Just about.

961
01:09:13,153 --> 01:09:16,031
FORD: From the look of the casings
on those Minuteman ICBMs...

962
01:09:16,198 --> 01:09:20,244
...the digital module's been bypassed
and you're prepping for full analog retrofit.

963
01:09:20,661 --> 01:09:22,246
Is my jaw supposed to drop?

964
01:09:22,412 --> 01:09:23,956
I get it. You're EOD.

965
01:09:24,122 --> 01:09:26,583
- I got my crew, they know what they're doing.
- Aim the pointy end...

966
01:09:26,750 --> 01:09:28,377
...at the monsters, right, sarge?

967
01:09:31,213 --> 01:09:34,258
When was the last time you let one of
your guys put their fingers in a live bomb?

968
01:09:35,133 --> 01:09:36,593
Look, this is what I do.

969
01:09:36,760 --> 01:09:38,178
This is my job.

970
01:09:39,388 --> 01:09:40,848
FORD:
Master sergeant.

971
01:09:41,098 --> 01:09:42,141
[SIGHS]

972
01:09:44,393 --> 01:09:46,145
My family's in the city.

973
01:09:47,729 --> 01:09:49,857
Okay? I need to get on that train.

974
01:09:50,482 --> 01:09:52,151
<i>WOMAN [OVER TV]:
You heard the spokesman say...</i>

975
01:09:52,317 --> 01:09:55,445
<i>... that the White House has not ruled
out the use of nuclear force.</i>

976
01:09:56,029 --> 01:09:57,364
[PHONE RINGING]

977
01:09:57,531 --> 01:09:59,491
WOMAN:
Sam, your mom's gonna be right back.

978
01:10:00,993 --> 01:10:02,619
Emergency, can I help you?

979
01:10:03,078 --> 01:10:04,121
Hello?

980
01:10:05,497 --> 01:10:06,957
Oh, yeah, just a sec.

981
01:10:07,666 --> 01:10:08,792
Elle, for you.

982
01:10:08,959 --> 01:10:11,336
- Tell them I'll be there in a minute.
- Elle.

983
01:10:11,837 --> 01:10:13,213
It's your husband.

984
01:10:17,259 --> 01:10:18,302
Hello?

985
01:10:18,468 --> 01:10:19,761
Elle?

986
01:10:20,596 --> 01:10:23,390
<i>Ford? Oh, God.</i>

987
01:10:23,557 --> 01:10:26,477
<i>- You all right? How's Sam?
- I've been calling you everywhere.</i>

988
01:10:26,643 --> 01:10:27,769
<i>- You okay?
- I'm fine.</i>

989
01:10:27,936 --> 01:10:31,190
<i>- I've got Sam with me.
- Great. Because I wanna get you both...</i>

990
01:10:31,356 --> 01:10:32,858
Can't believe this is happening.

991
01:10:33,942 --> 01:10:35,110
<i>Ford.</i>

992
01:10:35,277 --> 01:10:36,695
<i>You okay? Are you doing okay?</i>

993
01:10:37,029 --> 01:10:39,406
<i>I'm okay. Elle, please don't worry.</i>

994
01:10:39,573 --> 01:10:41,325
Baby, I'm so scared right now.

995
01:10:41,492 --> 01:10:42,534
<i>I know.</i>

996
01:10:44,453 --> 01:10:46,705
I'm gonna be at the hospital by sunrise.

997
01:10:47,414 --> 01:10:48,874
Then I'll get you and Sam out.

998
01:10:49,583 --> 01:10:50,626
Okay.

999
01:10:50,792 --> 01:10:52,961
<i>The military has a plan
to deal with these things.</i>

1000
01:10:53,587 --> 01:10:55,172
<i>I'm coming to get you both, okay?</i>

1001
01:10:55,339 --> 01:10:56,632
Okay.

1002
01:10:57,508 --> 01:10:59,134
Can you please just hurry?

1003
01:10:59,301 --> 01:11:01,386
<i>I will. Elle?</i>

1004
01:11:02,429 --> 01:11:04,640
I just wanted you to know that I love you.

1005
01:11:06,433 --> 01:11:09,686
[SOBBING]
I love you too. Just be safe.

1006
01:11:12,022 --> 01:11:13,273
I'll see you soon.

1007
01:11:15,275 --> 01:11:17,277
[WOMAN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY
OVER PA]

1008
01:11:20,906 --> 01:11:22,741
MAN:
Good to go! Let's move out!

1009
01:11:25,786 --> 01:11:28,247
[MEN SHOUTING INDISTINCTLY]

1010
01:11:33,919 --> 01:11:35,712
<i>MAN [OVER TV]:
As blackouts and electrical interference...</i>

1011
01:11:35,879 --> 01:11:37,464
<i>... radiate farther and farther west...</i>

1012
01:11:37,631 --> 01:11:41,301
<i>... citizens within 200 miles of the creature's
current sphere of influence...</i>

1013
01:11:41,468 --> 01:11:43,595
<i>... are being urged to please find shelter...</i>

1014
01:11:43,762 --> 01:11:46,140
<i>... stay indoors and stay off the roads.</i>

1015
01:11:46,306 --> 01:11:48,100
<i>DISPATCH [OVER PHONE]:
911, what's your emergency?</i>

1016
01:11:49,268 --> 01:11:50,769
<i>WOMAN:
- kids in the car.</i>

1017
01:11:50,936 --> 01:11:53,397
<i>WOMAN 2:
- debris going back about two miles.</i>

1018
01:11:53,564 --> 01:11:54,731
[WOMAN 3 SCREAMING
OVER PHONE]

1019
01:11:54,898 --> 01:11:56,775
<i>MAN:
This girl is not breathing.</i>

1020
01:11:58,485 --> 01:12:01,029
<i>MAN 2: ... people that are hurt.
Send somebody out here now!</i>

1021
01:12:01,780 --> 01:12:02,865
STENZ:
Yes, sir.

1022
01:12:04,032 --> 01:12:06,326
Yes, warheads are on the move.

1023
01:12:08,787 --> 01:12:10,497
I completely agree, sir.

1024
01:12:17,880 --> 01:12:19,214
All right, people. Let's go.

1025
01:12:19,381 --> 01:12:22,092
I need to know the exact location
of the MUTOs ASAP.

1026
01:12:22,259 --> 01:12:25,554
WOMAN: Aye. We're updating our
models with the current tracking data now.

1027
01:12:25,721 --> 01:12:26,889
Admiral.

1028
01:12:28,599 --> 01:12:29,641
Yes?

1029
01:12:31,643 --> 01:12:33,145
Please don't do this.

1030
01:12:35,147 --> 01:12:37,232
I understand your concerns, doctor.

1031
01:12:37,816 --> 01:12:39,193
But I am sacrificing lives...

1032
01:12:39,359 --> 01:12:42,821
...every minute trying to steer one of
these things clear of population centers...

1033
01:12:42,988 --> 01:12:44,656
...and now there are two more on the way.

1034
01:12:45,449 --> 01:12:48,619
There are millions of lives at risk.
So all I want to know...

1035
01:12:48,785 --> 01:12:49,870
...from you is:

1036
01:12:50,037 --> 01:12:52,456
Will it work and can they be killed?

1037
01:12:53,499 --> 01:12:54,917
SERIZAWA:
But we tried that before.

1038
01:12:55,083 --> 01:12:57,794
We're talking dialable yield.
Megatons, not kilotons.

1039
01:12:57,961 --> 01:12:59,630
Nothing can withstand that blast.

1040
01:12:59,796 --> 01:13:03,258
Makes the bomb we tried to kill it with
in '54 look like a firecracker.

1041
01:13:12,768 --> 01:13:14,520
[TRAIN HORN BLOWING]

1042
01:13:19,233 --> 01:13:22,069
FORD: Sergeant Morales. Give me a hand.
- I thought these nukes...

1043
01:13:22,236 --> 01:13:24,988
...all detonated by remote control.
- The MUTOs knock out...

1044
01:13:25,155 --> 01:13:26,365
...everything electric.

1045
01:13:26,532 --> 01:13:28,200
Including detonators.

1046
01:13:28,367 --> 01:13:31,078
Can't even get in range
without these things going haywire.

1047
01:13:31,453 --> 01:13:32,579
But this?

1048
01:13:32,746 --> 01:13:35,165
This, on the other hand, is old-school.

1049
01:13:35,332 --> 01:13:36,583
Clockwork.

1050
01:13:36,750 --> 01:13:37,793
MORALES:
Takes a licking...

1051
01:13:37,960 --> 01:13:39,253
...keeps on ticking.
FORD: Heh.

1052
01:13:42,881 --> 01:13:43,924
[ALL GASP]

1053
01:13:45,300 --> 01:13:47,344
[SCREECHING]

1054
01:13:48,762 --> 01:13:49,805
[TRAIN CREAKING]

1055
01:13:56,103 --> 01:13:57,146
Holy shit.

1056
01:13:57,312 --> 01:14:01,024
MAN: Sergeant Morales, get down here
with that radio. On the double. Move, move!

1057
01:14:03,569 --> 01:14:05,571
[GUNFIRE IN DISTANCE]

1058
01:14:07,865 --> 01:14:10,492
MAN: Snake Eyes,
this is Bravo to November. Is the bridge...

1059
01:14:10,659 --> 01:14:11,785
...clear? Over.

1060
01:14:11,952 --> 01:14:14,830
[GUNFIRE AND YELLING
OVER RADIO]

1061
01:14:14,997 --> 01:14:16,039
I say again:

1062
01:14:16,206 --> 01:14:17,958
We got a train of VIP cargo...

1063
01:14:18,125 --> 01:14:20,878
...headed for the coast.
Is the bridge clear? Over.

1064
01:14:22,004 --> 01:14:23,338
Snake Eyes, I need a sitrep.

1065
01:14:23,505 --> 01:14:24,965
Are the tracks clear?

1066
01:14:25,132 --> 01:14:29,136
We are at phase line yellow. In the next
10 mikes, we're advancing to phase line red.

1067
01:14:29,303 --> 01:14:30,846
Secure or not? Over.

1068
01:14:31,013 --> 01:14:32,890
[SCREAMING OVER RADIO]

1069
01:14:58,707 --> 01:15:00,209
You think it's intact?

1070
01:15:01,001 --> 01:15:02,836
Only one way to find out.

1071
01:15:03,003 --> 01:15:04,588
- You wanna take the top?
- Sure.

1072
01:15:04,755 --> 01:15:07,341
You check below. Sergeant Morales,
you come with me.

1073
01:15:11,136 --> 01:15:13,055
[BATS SCREECHING]

1074
01:15:29,571 --> 01:15:30,614
Shit.

1075
01:15:35,828 --> 01:15:37,204
Jesus.

1076
01:15:45,003 --> 01:15:46,547
[BOTH GRUNTING]

1077
01:15:49,800 --> 01:15:52,261
- Jones, you all right?
JONES: Yeah, I'm good!

1078
01:16:02,271 --> 01:16:03,730
[BLOWING WHISTLE]

1079
01:16:12,447 --> 01:16:13,782
The bridge is intact.

1080
01:16:13,949 --> 01:16:15,242
Bulldog, this is Eagle.

1081
01:16:15,409 --> 01:16:16,869
All clear to move out. Over.

1082
01:16:17,035 --> 01:16:18,620
<i>MAN [OVER RADIO]:
Roger that, Eagle.</i>

1083
01:16:21,540 --> 01:16:23,458
Let's go! Let's go, people!

1084
01:16:24,293 --> 01:16:26,378
[TRAIN HORN BLOWS]

1085
01:16:26,545 --> 01:16:27,838
[STATIC OVER RADIO]

1086
01:16:28,005 --> 01:16:29,047
Say again.

1087
01:16:29,214 --> 01:16:32,176
I do not have a visual.
What is your position? Over.

1088
01:16:32,801 --> 01:16:35,095
Unreadable. Say again. Over.

1089
01:16:36,054 --> 01:16:37,514
[GRUNTING]

1090
01:16:41,393 --> 01:16:42,811
Hit the deck.

1091
01:16:45,147 --> 01:16:47,149
[THUDDING]

1092
01:17:05,167 --> 01:17:07,127
[MUTO GROWLING]

1093
01:17:09,004 --> 01:17:10,881
[RADIO CRACKLING]

1094
01:17:12,716 --> 01:17:13,842
Help me turn it off, man.

1095
01:17:14,009 --> 01:17:16,345
[CREAKING]

1096
01:17:30,859 --> 01:17:32,194
[TRAIN HORN BLOWING]

1097
01:17:32,361 --> 01:17:34,363
[SHRIEKS]

1098
01:18:00,139 --> 01:18:01,765
Run!

1099
01:18:02,975 --> 01:18:04,017
Move it, run!

1100
01:18:04,184 --> 01:18:05,435
[PANTING]

1101
01:18:05,811 --> 01:18:07,020
Ford! Aah!

1102
01:18:14,820 --> 01:18:15,988
[TRAIN HORN BLOWS]

1103
01:18:17,948 --> 01:18:19,241
[GASPS]

1104
01:18:23,745 --> 01:18:26,165
[MUTO SHRIEKING]

1105
01:18:28,000 --> 01:18:29,459
[GASPING]

1106
01:18:43,390 --> 01:18:44,558
<i>MAN [OVER RADIO]:
He's going under!</i>

1107
01:18:45,392 --> 01:18:46,894
Boats, sound the collision alarm.

1108
01:18:47,060 --> 01:18:48,562
Frame 180.

1109
01:18:48,729 --> 01:18:50,147
[ALARM BLARING]

1110
01:18:59,573 --> 01:19:01,325
WOMAN:
We're losing visual, admiral.

1111
01:19:01,825 --> 01:19:02,993
He's diving.

1112
01:19:03,577 --> 01:19:07,414
Changing course and moving fast. I've
got him at 33 knots and picking up speed.

1113
01:19:07,581 --> 01:19:08,957
He's gonna outrun us, sir.

1114
01:19:09,583 --> 01:19:10,834
[EXHALES]

1115
01:19:19,134 --> 01:19:20,677
[BIRD SQUAWKING]

1116
01:19:31,104 --> 01:19:33,106
[COUGHING]

1117
01:20:01,760 --> 01:20:03,470
[MEN SHOUTING INDISTINCTLY]

1118
01:20:07,099 --> 01:20:08,350
MAN:
Watch the swinging!

1119
01:20:08,517 --> 01:20:09,893
MAN 2:
No swing!

1120
01:20:10,060 --> 01:20:11,103
Hey!

1121
01:20:14,231 --> 01:20:15,274
Hold on!

1122
01:20:15,941 --> 01:20:17,109
Medic!

1123
01:20:20,529 --> 01:20:23,824
<i>WOMAN [OVER TV]: They are insisting
civilians make their way to the BARTstations.</i>

1124
01:20:23,991 --> 01:20:26,702
<i>BARTstations are designated shelters.</i>

1125
01:20:26,869 --> 01:20:29,997
These patients are my responsibility.
Where are you taking them?

1126
01:20:30,164 --> 01:20:32,416
Across the bridges.
Critical and children only.

1127
01:20:32,583 --> 01:20:36,295
Shelters are gonna fill up fast.
Trust me, they'll be safer outside the city.

1128
01:20:37,212 --> 01:20:38,881
- I can take Sam.
ELLE: No, no, no.

1129
01:20:39,047 --> 01:20:40,090
Ford's on his way.

1130
01:20:40,257 --> 01:20:42,718
If you change your mind,
the buses leave in 10 minutes.

1131
01:20:44,803 --> 01:20:46,472
Come on. Where are you, Ford?

1132
01:20:47,181 --> 01:20:48,932
MAN:
This way! Keep them moving!

1133
01:20:51,143 --> 01:20:52,644
MAN 2:
Let's go. Come on, come on.

1134
01:21:02,196 --> 01:21:04,531
Hey! Where are they taking it?

1135
01:21:04,698 --> 01:21:07,367
Twenty miles offshore, convergence point.

1136
01:21:07,534 --> 01:21:09,411
We're gonna lure them there.

1137
01:21:10,245 --> 01:21:12,247
Three birds, one stone.

1138
01:21:30,140 --> 01:21:31,642
[SIREN CHIRPS]

1139
01:21:35,562 --> 01:21:36,980
[HORN HONKING]

1140
01:21:37,147 --> 01:21:38,273
ELLE:
Wait!

1141
01:21:40,275 --> 01:21:41,777
Okay, Sammy.

1142
01:21:41,944 --> 01:21:43,237
Laura, thank God.

1143
01:21:43,403 --> 01:21:46,281
Sammy, you remember Laura.
She's Mommy's work friend, right?

1144
01:21:46,824 --> 01:21:48,867
She's gonna look after you
for a little bit.

1145
01:21:49,034 --> 01:21:50,369
Daddy's gonna be here soon.

1146
01:21:50,536 --> 01:21:52,830
And I'm gonna just
come get you right after.

1147
01:21:52,996 --> 01:21:54,289
I promise.

1148
01:21:54,456 --> 01:21:55,541
Okay.

1149
01:21:56,124 --> 01:21:57,167
Okay?

1150
01:21:59,878 --> 01:22:02,214
LAURA: Come on, sweetheart.
You're gonna come with me.

1151
01:22:02,381 --> 01:22:03,882
Your mom's gonna stay and help.

1152
01:22:05,050 --> 01:22:07,302
Elle, I'm gonna take care of him, okay?

1153
01:22:07,469 --> 01:22:10,180
- Say, "Bye-bye, Mommy."
SAM: Bye, Mommy.

1154
01:22:39,501 --> 01:22:40,836
I got him! I got him!

1155
01:22:41,003 --> 01:22:42,337
Just sit down here.

1156
01:22:42,504 --> 01:22:43,672
Sit, sit.

1157
01:22:44,590 --> 01:22:45,632
Here.

1158
01:22:45,799 --> 01:22:47,050
Did you lose consciousness?

1159
01:22:47,217 --> 01:22:49,553
I'm okay. Really, I'm fine.

1160
01:22:53,807 --> 01:22:55,684
STENZ:
Sitrep, please. Location of targets?

1161
01:22:55,851 --> 01:22:58,520
Male MUTO was spotted
30 miles off the Farallon Islands.

1162
01:22:58,687 --> 01:23:01,273
Showing seismic activity
to the east near Livermore.

1163
01:23:01,440 --> 01:23:03,901
- Should be the female closing in.
- Where's Godzilla?

1164
01:23:04,067 --> 01:23:05,652
WOMAN:
Last contact was five hours ago.

1165
01:23:05,819 --> 01:23:09,156
Maintaining a bearing of 053 degrees,
descending below a depth of 10,000 feet.

1166
01:23:09,323 --> 01:23:10,407
Be here within the hour.

1167
01:23:10,574 --> 01:23:13,660
<i>MAN [OVER TV]: Residents are trying
to get out of the city any way they can.</i>

1168
01:23:15,162 --> 01:23:16,914
There's still buses on that bridge.

1169
01:23:21,126 --> 01:23:22,294
[HORNS HONKING]

1170
01:23:22,461 --> 01:23:24,046
WOMAN:
Come on!

1171
01:23:24,213 --> 01:23:25,547
[MAN SHOUTING INDISTINCTLY]

1172
01:23:25,714 --> 01:23:28,884
MAN:
Let's get those busses through. Let's go!

1173
01:23:31,929 --> 01:23:34,515
[INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER]

1174
01:23:34,681 --> 01:23:36,308
We're not gonna stop the buses here.

1175
01:23:36,475 --> 01:23:37,518
DRIVER:
What?

1176
01:23:37,684 --> 01:23:38,727
[KIDS YELLING]

1177
01:23:38,894 --> 01:23:40,854
I can't hear you. Oh, kids...

1178
01:23:41,021 --> 01:23:42,523
...please be quiet.

1179
01:23:46,485 --> 01:23:48,111
[RUMBLING]

1180
01:24:02,459 --> 01:24:04,962
MAN: Move into position till you have
a clean line of sight!

1181
01:24:05,128 --> 01:24:07,172
[FOG HORN BLOWING]

1182
01:24:12,928 --> 01:24:14,930
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

1183
01:24:17,975 --> 01:24:20,435
[ROARING IN DISTANCE]

1184
01:24:38,370 --> 01:24:39,955
[KIDS SCREAM]

1185
01:24:41,456 --> 01:24:43,458
[BIRDS SQUAWKING]

1186
01:24:46,962 --> 01:24:49,047
Portside! Two hundred meters!

1187
01:24:59,308 --> 01:25:00,350
Brace!

1188
01:25:07,483 --> 01:25:09,485
[PANTING]

1189
01:25:10,194 --> 01:25:11,653
MAN:
Hold your fire.

1190
01:25:11,820 --> 01:25:13,238
Hold your fire.

1191
01:25:19,870 --> 01:25:21,663
Holy shit.

1192
01:25:25,584 --> 01:25:27,294
[ALL SHOUTING]

1193
01:25:27,461 --> 01:25:28,504
Oh, shit!

1194
01:25:28,670 --> 01:25:31,131
- Hold on!
- Watch out!

1195
01:25:32,424 --> 01:25:33,842
Fire! Fire! Fire!

1196
01:25:34,593 --> 01:25:36,595
[ALARMS BLARING]

1197
01:25:38,472 --> 01:25:41,391
LAURA: Look out! Get down!
Get down in your seats!

1198
01:25:41,558 --> 01:25:42,643
Please! Get down!

1199
01:25:44,186 --> 01:25:46,438
DRIVER:
Get out of the way! Get out of the way!

1200
01:25:48,941 --> 01:25:49,983
Hey!

1201
01:25:56,490 --> 01:25:58,408
MAN:
Move out! Move, move, move!

1202
01:26:01,453 --> 01:26:04,665
Striker! There's civilians
on the bridge. Hold your fire!

1203
01:26:11,088 --> 01:26:12,131
MAN:
Open fire!

1204
01:26:12,297 --> 01:26:13,590
[GUNFIRE]

1205
01:26:13,757 --> 01:26:15,717
[ROARS]

1206
01:26:20,514 --> 01:26:22,432
[ALL SCREAMING]

1207
01:26:28,647 --> 01:26:29,690
[HORN HONKING]

1208
01:26:29,857 --> 01:26:30,899
DRIVER:
Move! Move!

1209
01:26:31,066 --> 01:26:32,651
[GROWLS]

1210
01:26:38,323 --> 01:26:40,617
[GODZILLA ROARING
AND KIDS SCREAMING]

1211
01:26:58,760 --> 01:27:01,722
- All right, get in there!
- Prepare to arm the device!

1212
01:27:01,889 --> 01:27:04,766
Ready! You got it?

1213
01:27:05,726 --> 01:27:06,977
I'm all set.

1214
01:27:09,897 --> 01:27:11,023
Arming keys!

1215
01:27:15,360 --> 01:27:17,821
Three! Two! One!

1216
01:27:17,988 --> 01:27:19,781
[MACHINERY RATTLING]

1217
01:27:21,909 --> 01:27:23,452
[EMP BLAST]

1218
01:27:28,624 --> 01:27:29,875
MAN:
What the hell was that?

1219
01:27:30,042 --> 01:27:31,084
MAN 2:
EMP.

1220
01:27:31,251 --> 01:27:33,420
Engine's stopped! We lost power!

1221
01:27:34,087 --> 01:27:35,881
[SIREN WAILING]

1222
01:27:37,007 --> 01:27:39,343
[MACHINERY LOSES POWER]

1223
01:27:53,690 --> 01:27:55,567
[ALL SCREAMING]

1224
01:27:56,860 --> 01:27:58,278
[PANTING]

1225
01:28:00,989 --> 01:28:02,866
[ALL YELLING]

1226
01:28:10,499 --> 01:28:11,792
[GRUNTING]

1227
01:28:15,254 --> 01:28:17,172
- You all right?
- Yeah.

1228
01:28:20,050 --> 01:28:21,301
[MUTO SHRIEKS]

1229
01:28:21,802 --> 01:28:23,804
- Fire!
- Incoming!

1230
01:28:34,731 --> 01:28:35,774
[SHRIEKS]

1231
01:28:45,576 --> 01:28:47,035
[ALL SCREAMING]

1232
01:28:52,583 --> 01:28:54,126
[GROWLING]

1233
01:29:24,364 --> 01:29:27,034
[BOTH GROWLING]

1234
01:30:00,192 --> 01:30:04,238
MAN: Sam Brody was checked into
the Oakland Coliseum shelter. He is safe.

1235
01:30:04,404 --> 01:30:07,074
No record of Elle Brody.
Never made it out of the city.

1236
01:30:07,241 --> 01:30:11,328
Well, check again. Please.
I told her to wait for me, and I didn't make it.

1237
01:30:11,495 --> 01:30:14,581
They are trying to get everyone downtown
into subway shelters.

1238
01:30:14,748 --> 01:30:16,458
I'm sure your wife is fine.

1239
01:30:16,625 --> 01:30:18,669
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

1240
01:30:19,962 --> 01:30:21,004
MAN:
Lieutenant Brody!

1241
01:30:21,171 --> 01:30:23,215
I'm looking for Lieutenant Brody.

1242
01:30:24,049 --> 01:30:25,926
- Are you Brody?
- Yes.

1243
01:30:26,093 --> 01:30:29,138
Okay. The male delivered the warhead
to the center of downtown.

1244
01:30:29,638 --> 01:30:33,934
That puts 100,000 civilians in the blast radius.
We can't stop it remotely.

1245
01:30:34,101 --> 01:30:38,230
A timer has been installed. The MUTOs are
frying electronics within a five-mile bubble.

1246
01:30:38,397 --> 01:30:40,149
Means approaching from ground
is not an option.

1247
01:30:40,524 --> 01:30:43,360
That's why we'll be conducting
a HALO insertion. Jumping altitude...

1248
01:30:43,527 --> 01:30:45,028
...will be 30,000 feet.

1249
01:30:45,195 --> 01:30:47,739
We just skate to the top and drop. Here.

1250
01:30:47,906 --> 01:30:51,827
And here. If you don't hit a skyscraper
on the way, meet at rally point Charlie.

1251
01:30:51,994 --> 01:30:54,746
- Right here. Good?
- Doctor, any guesses where to look?

1252
01:30:54,913 --> 01:30:56,165
SERIZAWA:
Underground.

1253
01:30:56,498 --> 01:30:58,208
If the MUTOs have spawned...

1254
01:30:58,375 --> 01:31:00,002
...they'll be building a nest.

1255
01:31:00,377 --> 01:31:03,922
Captain, when you find the warhead...

1256
01:31:04,089 --> 01:31:06,049
...how long to disarm it?
- Without seeing...

1257
01:31:06,216 --> 01:31:09,219
...the analog mod, I couldn't even guess.
FORD: Sixty seconds...

1258
01:31:09,386 --> 01:31:10,846
...if I can access it.

1259
01:31:11,305 --> 01:31:12,848
I retrofitted that device myself.

1260
01:31:13,307 --> 01:31:14,808
CAPTAIN:
Lieutenant Brody is our only...

1261
01:31:14,975 --> 01:31:17,060
...EOD tech to survive the train attack.

1262
01:31:17,394 --> 01:31:19,188
Well, it sounds like we could use you.

1263
01:31:19,521 --> 01:31:20,647
With all due respect...

1264
01:31:20,814 --> 01:31:24,776
...if that doesn't work, then what's Plan B?
- The waterfront...

1265
01:31:24,943 --> 01:31:26,904
...is located one klick downhill.

1266
01:31:27,070 --> 01:31:29,156
Get the bomb to the pier, onto a boat...

1267
01:31:29,323 --> 01:31:32,367
...and as far away from the city
as possible before it detonates.

1268
01:31:36,121 --> 01:31:37,498
Any questions?

1269
01:31:38,499 --> 01:31:39,541
- Dismissed.
- That's it.

1270
01:31:39,708 --> 01:31:40,751
Let's move.

1271
01:31:41,084 --> 01:31:42,294
Lieutenant?

1272
01:31:43,629 --> 01:31:45,380
They've already been briefed.

1273
01:31:45,547 --> 01:31:47,299
We have no extraction plan.

1274
01:31:47,466 --> 01:31:50,719
If you don't walk out,
you don't come back at all.

1275
01:31:51,637 --> 01:31:53,514
Sir, I'll do whatever it takes.

1276
01:32:11,782 --> 01:32:14,368
This alpha predator of yours, doctor...

1277
01:32:15,619 --> 01:32:17,996
...do you really think he has a chance?

1278
01:32:20,374 --> 01:32:24,253
The arrogance of man is thinking
nature is in our control...

1279
01:32:24,711 --> 01:32:26,588
...and not the other way around.

1280
01:32:31,260 --> 01:32:32,928
Let them fight.

1281
01:32:36,223 --> 01:32:37,975
[GROWLING IN DISTANCE]

1282
01:32:42,104 --> 01:32:43,814
[ALL SCREAMING]

1283
01:32:51,738 --> 01:32:52,781
[ALL SCREAM]

1284
01:33:05,502 --> 01:33:07,379
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

1285
01:33:13,677 --> 01:33:15,012
[ALL SCREAMING]

1286
01:33:27,107 --> 01:33:29,109
MAN:
Oh, Lord God, we give thanks...

1287
01:33:29,276 --> 01:33:31,278
...for the opportunities you have given us...

1288
01:33:31,445 --> 01:33:34,364
...going together as comrades
to defend our great nation.

1289
01:33:34,531 --> 01:33:37,868
We thank you for the time and service
that you have given us together.

1290
01:33:38,035 --> 01:33:40,120
Now as we are about to leave one another...

1291
01:33:40,287 --> 01:33:42,247
...let us have the strength...

1292
01:33:56,720 --> 01:33:58,722
[ALARM BLARING]

1293
01:34:12,611 --> 01:34:14,613
[WIND WHISTLING]

1294
01:34:32,923 --> 01:34:34,925
[ALARM BEEPING]

1295
01:35:06,498 --> 01:35:08,500
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

1296
01:35:19,678 --> 01:35:21,680
[PANTING THROUGH MASK]

1297
01:36:07,601 --> 01:36:09,019
[PANTING]

1298
01:36:28,997 --> 01:36:31,542
MAN:
Take position! Take position!

1299
01:36:33,794 --> 01:36:35,212
I saw Team 1 move to the east.

1300
01:36:36,713 --> 01:36:39,758
Two of our team members didn't make it.
I heard bits and pieces on the radio.

1301
01:36:39,925 --> 01:36:41,635
Snipers on the rooftop
moving into position.

1302
01:36:42,094 --> 01:36:44,471
- Here we go. Picking up the nuke.
- Which way?

1303
01:36:44,638 --> 01:36:45,848
One klick up the hill.

1304
01:36:46,014 --> 01:36:47,057
We found the warhead.

1305
01:36:47,224 --> 01:36:49,393
Let's go! Up the hill, this direction. Move.

1306
01:37:03,073 --> 01:37:05,075
[TRACKER BEEPING]

1307
01:37:13,625 --> 01:37:15,002
Hey. Hey.

1308
01:37:15,419 --> 01:37:16,545
Look.

1309
01:37:21,049 --> 01:37:22,259
[PLOPPING NOISES]

1310
01:37:28,640 --> 01:37:30,934
[MUTO SHRIEKS]

1311
01:38:05,636 --> 01:38:07,638
[ROARING]

1312
01:38:15,604 --> 01:38:17,189
[GROWLS]

1313
01:38:28,367 --> 01:38:30,118
MAN:
Let's move, let's move.

1314
01:38:30,285 --> 01:38:31,495
On my six.

1315
01:38:48,762 --> 01:38:50,514
[ALL YELLING]

1316
01:38:58,397 --> 01:39:00,899
Sarge, get a look at this.

1317
01:39:04,069 --> 01:39:06,155
We gotta get moving.
You got a signal yet?

1318
01:39:06,321 --> 01:39:07,364
I got it.

1319
01:39:08,323 --> 01:39:09,366
[BEEPING]

1320
01:39:09,533 --> 01:39:10,576
It's down there.

1321
01:39:12,369 --> 01:39:13,954
[BEEPING INCREASES]

1322
01:39:19,376 --> 01:39:20,419
All right, move, move!

1323
01:39:29,136 --> 01:39:30,512
Grab a line!

1324
01:39:35,225 --> 01:39:36,560
More light. Grazer.

1325
01:39:46,820 --> 01:39:48,822
[BABIES SQUEAKING]

1326
01:39:57,873 --> 01:39:59,708
[SQUEAKING CONTINUES]

1327
01:40:00,626 --> 01:40:01,668
Right, clear out.

1328
01:40:01,835 --> 01:40:02,878
Here we go.

1329
01:40:03,545 --> 01:40:04,713
Whoa, look out, heads up!

1330
01:40:05,547 --> 01:40:06,590
How much time we got left?

1331
01:40:09,092 --> 01:40:11,011
We have 27 mikes.

1332
01:40:11,678 --> 01:40:13,472
We gotta get this thing down.

1333
01:40:19,019 --> 01:40:21,021
[CAR ALARM BEEPING]

1334
01:40:33,367 --> 01:40:34,952
[GODZILLA SHRIEKS]

1335
01:40:38,372 --> 01:40:40,374
[ALL YELLING]

1336
01:40:42,543 --> 01:40:44,419
MAN:
Move, move, I got you!

1337
01:40:44,586 --> 01:40:45,796
Move it out, move it out!

1338
01:40:48,132 --> 01:40:50,050
[GROWLING]

1339
01:40:50,884 --> 01:40:51,927
[SHRIEKS]

1340
01:41:10,946 --> 01:41:12,781
[ROARS]

1341
01:41:20,038 --> 01:41:21,665
MAN:
Careful! Careful.

1342
01:41:21,832 --> 01:41:23,417
And down in three...

1343
01:41:23,584 --> 01:41:25,669
...two, one.

1344
01:41:25,836 --> 01:41:27,045
Let's get this cover off.

1345
01:41:27,212 --> 01:41:28,255
Lieutenant, you're up.

1346
01:41:32,885 --> 01:41:35,387
It's not budging. It's sealed shut.

1347
01:41:35,554 --> 01:41:36,597
We need time to open it.

1348
01:41:36,763 --> 01:41:39,308
We don't have time! Let's haul it out.
We gotta get it on a boat.

1349
01:41:39,475 --> 01:41:41,143
Grab the warhead! Let's move!

1350
01:41:41,310 --> 01:41:42,352
Go!

1351
01:41:43,896 --> 01:41:44,938
Easy.

1352
01:41:46,148 --> 01:41:47,191
Easy, easy.

1353
01:41:48,400 --> 01:41:49,985
Move it out, guys!

1354
01:41:51,236 --> 01:41:52,863
[SQUEAKING]

1355
01:41:54,364 --> 01:41:55,949
MAN:
Lieutenant, let's go!

1356
01:41:56,116 --> 01:41:57,159
[GRUNTS]

1357
01:42:10,964 --> 01:42:12,257
[ROARS]

1358
01:42:30,734 --> 01:42:32,736
[MEN SHOUTING INDISTINCTLY]

1359
01:42:35,113 --> 01:42:36,323
MAN:
Lieutenant?

1360
01:42:40,619 --> 01:42:41,870
[GRUNTS]

1361
01:43:05,936 --> 01:43:07,479
[SNARLS]

1362
01:43:08,355 --> 01:43:10,023
[GROWLING]

1363
01:43:15,445 --> 01:43:17,447
[MAN SHOUTING INDISTINCTLY]

1364
01:43:36,175 --> 01:43:38,135
[HOWLING]

1365
01:43:48,228 --> 01:43:49,605
[GRUNTING]

1366
01:44:17,716 --> 01:44:20,135
[ATOMIC BREATH WHIRRING]

1367
01:44:31,522 --> 01:44:32,648
What the hell was that?

1368
01:44:32,815 --> 01:44:34,274
Holy shit! Did you see that?

1369
01:44:55,587 --> 01:44:56,672
This way.

1370
01:44:59,133 --> 01:45:00,467
Faster, faster.

1371
01:45:02,553 --> 01:45:04,096
Let's get this thing started.

1372
01:45:06,306 --> 01:45:07,391
Find the ignition, sir?

1373
01:45:07,766 --> 01:45:09,143
Give me that pack.

1374
01:45:09,560 --> 01:45:10,769
Here you go.

1375
01:45:12,896 --> 01:45:14,523
Come on, come on. Hurry.

1376
01:45:14,690 --> 01:45:16,525
[CRACKLING]

1377
01:45:16,692 --> 01:45:19,278
[MACHINE STARTING]

1378
01:45:19,444 --> 01:45:21,155
[ALARM SOUNDING]

1379
01:45:40,799 --> 01:45:42,676
Hurry it up. Let's go, let's go!

1380
01:45:44,094 --> 01:45:45,554
She's coming for the bomb!

1381
01:45:48,849 --> 01:45:50,934
Let's get this weapon secured.

1382
01:46:54,248 --> 01:46:56,083
[WHIMPERING]

1383
01:47:05,759 --> 01:47:07,427
[PANTING]

1384
01:47:10,139 --> 01:47:11,849
[GRUNTING]

1385
01:47:39,460 --> 01:47:40,919
[GUNFIRE IN DISTANCE]

1386
01:47:42,880 --> 01:47:44,882
[MEN SHOUTING INDISTINCTLY]

1387
01:47:57,603 --> 01:47:59,271
[GROWLS]

1388
01:48:07,988 --> 01:48:09,781
[GROANING]

1389
01:48:28,884 --> 01:48:30,135
[GRUNTS]

1390
01:48:36,099 --> 01:48:38,393
Unh! Come on.

1391
01:48:39,019 --> 01:48:40,062
Come on.

1392
01:48:46,860 --> 01:48:48,278
[BEEPING]

1393
01:48:49,112 --> 01:48:50,155
[ENGINE STARTS]

1394
01:48:56,703 --> 01:48:58,080
[GRUNTING]

1395
01:49:06,797 --> 01:49:08,340
[MACHINERY LOSES POWER]

1396
01:49:36,702 --> 01:49:38,495
[GROWLING]

1397
01:49:44,793 --> 01:49:46,628
[ATOMIC BREATH WHIRRING]

1398
01:49:58,015 --> 01:49:59,975
[ROARING]

1399
01:50:14,406 --> 01:50:16,116
[MACHINERY POWERS UP]

1400
01:50:38,180 --> 01:50:39,807
[EXHALES]

1401
01:50:41,934 --> 01:50:43,727
[FAINT ROARING]

1402
01:50:55,113 --> 01:50:56,990
[BOMB TICKING]

1403
01:51:03,330 --> 01:51:04,748
[EXHALES]

1404
01:52:26,371 --> 01:52:28,373
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

1405
01:52:56,777 --> 01:52:58,779
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

1406
01:53:03,075 --> 01:53:04,535
WOMAN:
Stay right here.

1407
01:53:10,499 --> 01:53:11,583
<i>FIREMAN:
Quiet!</i>

1408
01:53:12,084 --> 01:53:13,127
Quiet!

1409
01:53:13,961 --> 01:53:16,004
I hear some people. Come on!

1410
01:53:17,297 --> 01:53:20,217
This one's in bad shape.
Come on, grab my hand. We got you.

1411
01:53:20,384 --> 01:53:22,177
Help him up. Help him up.

1412
01:53:22,344 --> 01:53:25,013
<i>MAN [OVER PA]:
Attention, new arrivals:</i>

1413
01:53:25,180 --> 01:53:27,766
<i>Please proceed to the marked tables...</i>

1414
01:53:27,933 --> 01:53:30,394
<i>...for registration.
WOMAN: Let's make some room, please!</i>

1415
01:53:30,561 --> 01:53:31,645
MAN:
Mary!

1416
01:53:32,062 --> 01:53:33,105
BO Y:
Daddy!

1417
01:53:33,272 --> 01:53:35,065
[BABY CRYING]

1418
01:53:58,297 --> 01:53:59,882
[GODZILLA GRUNTING]

1419
01:54:14,605 --> 01:54:15,772
Sam.

1420
01:54:20,861 --> 01:54:22,112
SAM:
Mommy!

1421
01:54:22,279 --> 01:54:23,363
Sammy?

1422
01:54:24,823 --> 01:54:26,158
[SOBBING]

1423
01:54:26,909 --> 01:54:28,118
Mommy! Mommy!

1424
01:54:28,285 --> 01:54:29,703
Sweetpea.

1425
01:54:30,746 --> 01:54:32,206
Hi!

1426
01:54:33,499 --> 01:54:35,042
Hi, baby.

1427
01:54:56,939 --> 01:54:57,981
FORD:
Hi.

1428
01:55:03,070 --> 01:55:04,363
Oh, baby.

1429
01:55:04,530 --> 01:55:07,074
[CROWD CHEERING]

1430
01:55:35,018 --> 01:55:37,563
[ROARING]

1431
02:03:02,966 --> 02:03:04,968
[English - US - SDH]
